title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: green chili stew
directions: Saute meat and onions until brown; drain off fat. Add seasoning and enough hot water to cover meat and potatoes, about 2 inches. Simmer until meat is tender. More water may be added if needed. Serve with flour tortillas.

title: brownie camp-out shaker butter
directions: Pour heavy cream into a large jar; add sour cream.
Cover jar tightly and shake hard, taking turns until a lump of soft butter forms.
Pour off liquid.
Place in saucer and press out any last bit of water remaining in butter.
Add a little salt.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Generously grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Blend sugar, corn syrup, butter flavor Crisco and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat 2 minutes or until light and foamy, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add popcorn, tossing to coat.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake for 8 minutes. Turn and toss.
Return to oven an additional 7 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Break into bite size pieces.

title: green tomato relish
directions: After chopping green tomatoes, put in cheesecloth or colander and mash juice out. Then put all ingredients in large pot and bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 30 minutes or until thick. Spoon hot mixture into hot sterilized jars. Cover at once with metal jar lids and bands. Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: tamale dip
directions: Chop tamales.
Add chili and cheese; heat in crock-pot, until all is dissolved.
Serve dip hot with vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: hot dog burrito
directions: In large frypan, add 1 tablespoon oil and saute onion.
Add sliced hot dogs and fry until lightly browned.
Add 1 can tomato sauce and red pepper; cook until thickened.
Place spoonful on tortilla.
Add cheese if you like.
Roll up and enjoy.

title: bread rolls
directions: Put flour
and sugar in large bowl.
Make well and add water and yeast.
Let
set
until
yeast is dissolved.
Beat eggs, potatoes, lard and salt well.
Stir into first mixture.
Let set on counter overnight. Roll out and
cut with biscuit cutter.
Let raise 2 to 3 hours and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Stir ingredients together with spoon until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls into muffin pan.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: quick and easy bake custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until firm in middle.
Makes own crust.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then mix in the shortening and mix until looks like corn meal.

Then add the buttermilk and mix together and dump on a piece of foil with some flour scattered on it and knead just enough to work with the dough and pat to thickness desired and cut out and place on greased cookie sheet. Then bake for about 20 minutes at 425°.

title: microwave peanut-popcorn balls
directions: Mix brown sugar, corn syrup, peanut butter and salt in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 minute and 30 seconds or until mixture begins to bubble.
Stir.
Stir in popcorn and peanuts until well coated.
Let stand 5 minutes. Shape mixture firmly into four 3-inch balls with hands dipped in cold water. Place on waxed paper.
Let stand about 30 minutes or until completely cool.
Wrap each in plastic wrap.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Shape into nickle size balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Make crust and spread in bottom of a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices; mix well.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies or 10 to 11 minutes for crisp cookies. Cool one minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Store tightly covered.
(I always cook one pan without raisins first because Kathy doesn't like them, but Robert does.)

title: chocolate squares
directions: Line large cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
Put crackers on foil.
Bring margarine and brown sugar to boil.
Boil 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.

title: pear salad
directions: Mix cherries, cream cheese and pecans and spoon onto pears.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bearnaise sauce
directions: Combine wine, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, shallots and tarragon in saucepan and simmer very slowly for about 5 minutes. Heat water in bottom of a double boiler over very low heat until just simmering. Strain previous mixture and place the liquid in top section of boiler. In a separate bowl, beat the egg yolks with about 1 tablespoon butter; then add slowly to mixture in boiler, while continuously whisking. Add 1/2 teaspoon at a time of remaining butter while slowly and constantly whisking until the emulsion is formed. As the emulsion is forming, the egg will be cooked, not scrambled. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, salad oil and eggs well.
Add carrots, walnuts and pineapple.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion and margarine together, then add the broccoli. Cook until soft.
Heat soup and water, then mix with broccoli. Add the Cheez Whiz.
Add 1/2 cup of the cooked rice.
Put in a buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dorthy's goulash
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add ground beef and brown.
Season. While onion and meat are browning, cook macaroni.
Stir macaroni into meat mixture.
Add tomato soup and water.
Simmer in heavy skillet, covered, 15 minutes.
Serve with lettuce salad and corn bread.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Add half and half and the Velveeta.
Heat until the Velveeta is completely melted.

title: baked pumpkin in shell
directions: Cut top from pumpkin; reserve for lid.
Scoop out seeds and fiber; discard.
Combine remaining ingredients in large saucepan; stir over low flame until liquid begins to simmer.
Place pumpkin on a large sheet of heavy foil in baking pan.
Pour hot liquid into pumpkin and place lid on top.
Pull up foil to enclose pumpkin loosely and fold to close openings.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove pan from oven and let stand; pumpkin keeps warm 3 to 4 hours, may be served warm or cooled.

title: french meat pie
directions: Mix hamburg, pork, onions and spices.
Cook for 1/2 hour, breaking up meat.
Add crackers (chopped fine with rolling pin); place in pie shell.
Poke holes in top of crust; bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix until doughy.
Drop in boiling water.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles, rinsing each can of soup with a small amount of water. Bake 1 hour at 250° to 300°.
If desired, you can sprinkle noodles over the top and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pinn's
directions: Mix up.
Serve that evening.
Can make ahead of time.
If you have fresh mint, add the leaves on top before serving.

title: julie's chocolate cookie cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
In a saucepan, combine water, margarine, cocoa and shortening.
Let come to a rolling boil.
Pour over flour mixture and mix together. In a small bowl, mix eggs, vanilla, soda and buttermilk.
Combine with other mixture and pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and nuts.
Add oil, carrots and pineapple. Add eggs, then vanilla.
This should take 5 minutes beating. Bake in greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans for an hour at 350°.

title: holiday spiced tea
directions: In tea pot, put in tea bags, cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Fill pot with boiling water and steep for 30 minutes.
Then remove tea bags, cloves and cinnamon sticks and stir in sugar until dissolved.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Lightly beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients except mini morsels.
Stir just until moistened.
Fold in mini morsels.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool a few minutes and brush with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef with egg, onion and spices.
Add grated potato.
Form into meatballs and brown slowly in frying pan. Drain fat.

title: twice baked cheese potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well. Rub skins with shortening and pierce in several places to allow steam to escape. Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: custard peach pie
directions: You will also need an 8-inch pie pan.

title: ice cream coffee
directions: Make coffee and chill.
Whip the cream.
Add to coffee.
Serve in chilled cups with a spoon of ice cream.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant.
Dice eggplant in cubes and cook in water for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain off water.
Spread eggplant in casserole. Mix 1/2 of Parmesan cheese in spaghetti sauce; pour over eggplant.
Sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put rice on bottom.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soups and 1 can water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks.
Add sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and rice.
Stiffly beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Turn into baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: eggs strade(great for sunday brunch)
directions: Use large bowl.
Brown sausage; crumble and drain.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add mustard and salt.
With spoon, mix in cheese.
Fold in sausage and bread.
Grease 9 x 11-inch pan; pour in mix and let sit overnight in fridge.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split pie(makes 4 servings)
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Layer pie in order of ingredients.
Chill.
A low calorie recipe.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine lemonade and milk.
Fold in topping.
Pour into pie shell (baked).
Chill at least 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute
mushrooms,
onion
and shrimp in 2 tablespoons of butter
until shrimp is just pink, no more than 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes,
salt,
pepper
and paprika.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir
in sherry and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine cream and
flour into smooth paste.
Stir into shrimp mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring, and simmer for 1 minute.
Add rice and mix gently
over
low
heat.
Pour into buttered 2 quart casserole. Melt
remaining butter and combine with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over
casserole
and
place
under
broiler a few minutes until slightly browned.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl until bound together. Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: raw fries
directions: Cook potatoes in microwave for 10 to 12 minutes, then thinly slice them.
Heat shortening in 10-inch skillet until melted. Layer 1/3 each of potatoes and onion in skillet; sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Repeat twice.
Dot top layer with margarine.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes. Uncover and cook turning once until potatoes are brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place vegetables and broth in saucepan.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 8 minutes.
Mix milk, cornstarch, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add to cooked vegetables and cook, stirring constantly, until soup is lightly thickened and mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Makes 4 servings of 1 cup each.
Calories per serving: 115.

title: christmas salad
directions: Bring 1 c. water to a boil.
Add cranberry sauce and heat until it melts.
Add jello and stir.
Add 1 c. cold water.
Chill until mixture is syrupy.
Add orange sections to jello.
Pour into ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves and fill center with creamed cottage cheese.
One c. canned mandarin oranges can be used.

title: cherry angel delight
directions: Cut cake into small cubes; place half of cubes in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Spoon pie filling over cake, reserving half cup for garnish.
Cover with remaining cake cubes.
Mix pudding, milk and sour cream together until smooth and pour over cake.
Garnish with reserved pie filling.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar; add vanilla and salt. Add eggs.
Beat well after each egg.
Stir in sifted flour; mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned on edges.
Remove immediately from pan.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with layer of whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk and blend in whipped topping. Pour 1/2 of the pudding over graham crackers.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers and pour remaining pudding mixture over top.
Cover with layer of graham crackers and refrigerate 3 hours, then frost.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: If using fresh broccoli, wash, stem and remove leaves.
Place in a large pan; add 1/2 of the stock.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 7 minutes or until broccoli is tender. Remove broccoli from stock and chop coarsely.
Add the remaining stock, ham, salt, pepper and 2 cups half and half to stock in pan. Stir well, bring to boil over medium heat.

title: e z pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Empty pineapple and juice into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover pan bottom evenly.
Top with cake mix; spread evenly.
Dot cake mix layer with slices of butter stick (about 15 to 20 slices).
Bake for 35 minutes for glass dish, 40 minutes for metal pan, until top is golden brown.
Let cool for 10 to 15 minutes before slicing pieces.
Good alone or topped with ice cream.

title: my mother's orange cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Add alternately with milk, juices and vanilla. Pour into well-greased Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour at 320°. Pour glaze over warm cake.

title: taco dip
directions: First Layer: Large can refried beans

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. (This recipe was given to me by Lorene Taylor and it is the absolute best chocolate pound cake EVER!)

title: jello dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine Jell-O and Cool Whip. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: heavenly pineapple dessert
directions: Blend Cool Whip and lite cream cheese. Place pineapple on crust as thin layer and then top with Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with crushed walnuts.

title: mama's oven caramel corn
directions: Heat butter, sugar, syrup and salt until bubbly.
Continue cooking on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir until foamy.
Pour over corn and peanuts.
Stir until all coated.
Bake in 200° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven and continue stirring until cool.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring to a boil salt, oleo and water.
Add flour; remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg. Spread dough in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Add cream cheese. Spread over cooled crust.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice in mixer until creamy.
Pour into pie shell.
Add cherries.
Chill.

title: make ahead breakfast bake
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and cook until brown.
Drain. Sprinkle bread in buttered baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine milk, eggs and seasonings.
Beat well and pour over sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Put corns in medium bowl. Blend flour, sugar, margarine, salt and eggs in a blender, add corn. Stir in green pepper and pimentos, add cheese. Pour into a casserole dish and bake 1 hour. Pudding is done when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello with boiling water.
Add pineapple juice.
Pour into 1-gallon jug and freeze.
Thaw slightly.
Put into punch bowl and add Sprite.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Put sauerkraut in 1 1/2 quart casserole; top with corned beef and cover with cheese.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix slightly beaten egg, sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts on top and pat down.
Pour melted butter over nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until mixture is set.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill milk 3 hours.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cups hot water. Chill until thick and then beat until fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Beat milk until thick.
Add first mixture.
Sprinkle half of the crumbs into 13
x9-inch pan.
Pour in mixture and cover top with other half of crumbs.
Chill until firm.

title: orange pudding
directions: *Use rind of 1 orange and pulp and juice of all 3.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over quick cooking oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes.
While standing cream together the shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla and salt.
Add creamed mixture to oatmeal mixture.
Beat well.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Mix together the ingredients listed.
Pour half of batter in a big skillet.
Layer meat and remaining corn bread mix.
Bake slowly at 250° to 300° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix melted margarine, flour and pecans.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until brown.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread on crust. Top with pie filling, then top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: gallania barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients together in saucepan.
Keep hot as needed before serving.
Yields 4 cups sauce.

title: figs dried in syrup
directions: First Day:
Wash figs and prick each with a fork.
Make syrup of sugar, water, Karo and lemon slices.
Bring to a boil in heavy pan and carefully lay figs in syrup.
Cover and bring to boil again.
Lower heat and boil gently for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and allow to cool overnight, turning figs once or twice in syrup.

title: table syrup
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and cook until it thickens slightly. When cool, add vanilla or maple flavoring.

title: mom's chicken casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. In a greased casserole dish, alternate layers of broccoli, chicken and sauce.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in
boiling water and add beet juice, vinegar and
salt.
When this is cool, add the beets, nuts and other ingredients.
Mold
in
individual
molds
or in a salad mold ring.
Makes 8 servings.
Very good with meats.

title: "delicious" rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Put into pan as directed.
Then on top of unbaked cake, add rhubarb.
Over top of that, sprinkle sugar, then pour whipping cream over top of cake.
Bake until done.
No frosting needed.

title: crab dip
directions: Place cream cheese on platter.
Drain crab meat and place on cheese; top with cocktail sauce.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: chili with rice
directions: Cook and stir meat, pepper, and seasoning in large skillet on medium heat until meat is brown.
Stir in water, beans, and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in corn.
Return to boil. Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Stir.
Top with cheese.

title: molasses cupcakes
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, shortening and salt together and keep 1/3 cup for the topping.
In another bowl, mix the molasses, hot water and baking soda.
Beat in flour mixture.
Put in cupcake pans.
Put the 1/3 cup topping on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear. Simmer broccoli in about 1 cup water for 5 to 7 minutes; do not drain. Add onion and remaining ingredients. Stir and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Garnish with shredded cheese and parsley.

title: orange glazed pecans
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients on stove over medium heat; bring to boil.
Boil for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the pecans; cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; continue stirring until pecans fall separately and have a sugar white coating on them.
Let cool on wax paper for 30 minutes.

title: creamed chicken on corn bread waffles
directions: Combine undiluted chicken soup, diced chicken, cooked and drained vegetables and chives or onions
in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Keep hot while baking waffles.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date-nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sift flour with baking powder and salt; set aside.
In small bowl of electric mixer at medium speed, beat eggs until light. Gradually add granulated sugar, beating until smooth and fluffy. At low speed, beat in flour mixture until well combined.
Stir in dates and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Spread evenly in prepared pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden.
Cool slightly.
With sharp knife, cut into bars while still warm.
Let cool completely in pan before removing.
To serve, roll in confectioners sugar. Makes 30.

title: taco lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, cook the beef, green pepper and onion over medium heat until meat in no longer pink; drain. Add water and taco seasoning; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 2 minutes.
Stir in black beans and tomatoes. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and crumble while cooking.
Drain excess fat and place in large bowl.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in skillet sausage was cooked in.
Add sausage, soups, rice and water.
Mix well and place in 11 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Can be frozen.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pickles - sweet and sour
directions: Put pickles in jars.
Mix water, sugar, vinegar and salt. Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over jars and water bath until the pickles begin to change color.
This makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Place in container, cover and chill. Best if prepared ahead of time.

title: aunt donna's hamburger beans
directions: "You get some bread first and warm it and then put wiener on it and then put the mayonnaise and ketchup on it and then put it in the oven and cook it for 2 hours and then let it cool and put it in a plate and eat it."

title: chunk-style applesauce
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Ingredients can be adjusted, depending on the kind of apple used and the amount of applesauce wanted.
This freezes well for future use.
Mash with potato masher for a slightly smoother consistency.

title: stuffed strawberries with almond creme
directions: Beat pudding, milk, whipping cream and almond extract.
Cut tips of strawberries in a (+), but not all the way through.
Pipe filling into center of strawberry.
Makes pretty flowerets.

title: tuna burgers
directions: In a bowl, combine tuna, bread crumbs, celery, Miracle Whip, onion, chili sauce and egg. Shape into 4 patties. Melt butter in a skillet. Cook patties for about 45 minutes per side or until lightly browned. Serve on buns with lettuce and tomato, if desired.

title: robyn's yellow cookie bars
directions: Blend these ingredients and put on top of "crust".
Sprinkle with 1/2 c. chopped nuts.
Bake 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: mustard sauce for ham
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the oil very slowly.
Keep heating until smooth. Serve with the cooked or baked ham.

title: ground beef 'n beans casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef and strain.
Stir in all ingredients except biscuits and cheese.
Heat until bubbly, then pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits into halves and place around edges of mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large bowl mix well salad oil, eggs and sugar.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder. Stir in nuts and chopped apples.
Mix well.
Spread mixture in a greased 11 x 9-inch pan.
Distribute butterscotch chips on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
For best results, bake 1 day before serving.

title: oven fried chicken and dressing
directions: Season chicken to taste and brown in fat.
Combine crumbs, seasonings, onion and butter; mix well.
Add soup to pan drippings to make gravy.
Arrange chicken in Dutch oven.
Pile dressing in center.
Pour gravy over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: light and fruity jello
directions: Completely dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir about 3 minutes.
Add ice and stir until Jell-O thickens.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using a wire whisk, blend in whip cream.
Whip until very smooth.
Add fruit and refrigerate until firm.

title: butter crust rolls
directions: Combine milk, eggs and yeast.
Combine dry ingredients. Add to
yeast
mixture.
Add
shortening.
Mix with a mixer 7 minutes. Turn
dough
out
onto floured surface.
Roll into a rectangle. Pat
softened
margarine onto 2/3 dough.
Fold the unbuttered third of dough over the next third, then fold that third
over the first third.
Roll again into a rectangle and repeat
the process
more
times.
Chill dough at least 12 hours,
but
not more
than 24 hours.
(Dough can be frozen.) Make into desired shapes and bake at 375° until done.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain and add soup, milk and butter.
Simmer.
Add shredded cheese, melt and serve.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Cake:
Combine pudding mix, vanilla and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer. Lightly oil a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place a layer of whole graham crackers in dish.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers. Cover with cooled topping.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites (high speed) 1 minute.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Continue beating until egg whites are just stiff enough to hold shape.
Add sugar slowly (medium speed).
Add vanilla. Continue beating (high speed) for 2 minutes or until mixture will stand in stiff peaks.
Mix sugar and flour.
Gradually add to egg whites (low speed).
Continue mixing 2 minutes after last addition. Pour into 3 ungreased tube cake pans.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350° for 35 minutes at 400°.
Immediately upon removal from oven, invert cake to cool.

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins
directions: Beat egg well.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into 12 greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dusty cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly oil a 10x15 inch baking pan or cookie sheet. Spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Place cauliflower in a large plastic bag. Drizzle with oil and shake until cauliflower is evenly coated.
Combine remaining ingredients and place in bag. Shake again until
well coated. Spread cauliflower on prepared sheet. Sprinkle with any remaining crumbs. Bake 18 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Boil the butter and sugar for 2 minutes.
Next place graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Pour mixture over crackers; add nuts. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: kringla
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Combine liquids and egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture alternately with liquids.
Knead dough lightly on board until smooth.
Add a little flour when needed.
Roll into strips about 1/2-inch thick, 8 inches long. Twist into figure 8.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until tan. Serve like rolls, buttered.

title: award-winning brisket
directions: Marinate the ingredients for 2 or 3 days; turn each day.
Bake in liquid 4 hours or until tender at 300°.
Baste occasionally or turn over, cover while baking, until last hour, remove cover and if you wish, pour 1/2 cup barbecue sauce over brisket.
Increase oven temperature to 350°.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, cornmeal, vanilla, butter and vinegar. Mix well and let stand for 10 minutes, then stir gently. Put into the unbaked pie shell. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemonade
directions: In 1-quart jar with tight fitting lid, shake sugar and lemon peel with
1 1/2 cups very hot water until sugar is dissolved. Add lemon juice and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: mom's favorite snack mix
directions: Need one large bowl and let your children mix together. Smiles will follow!

title: jalapeno grits casserole
directions: Place water and 1 teaspoon salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Stir in 1 cup regular grits.
Reduce heat to lowest setting and cook, covered, 5 to 20 minutes (while grits will be cooked in 5 minutes, they are much better after 20 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Generously butter a deep 2-quart baking dish. Place grits in large bowl.
Add cheese and butter and beat until smooth.
Stir in beaten eggs and jalapeno peppers and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into prepared baking dish.
Bake at 350° until grits are set and top is lightly browned, about 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix together bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add egg and butter or shortening.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator and use as desired.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
When ready to make muffins, fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen muffins.

title: homemade chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: gourmet baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
When cool enough to handle, but not cold, cut in half.
Scoop out potato, leaving peel intact.
Mix with butter, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stuff peels with potato mixture.
Bake at 400° until heated.
Sprinkle bacon crumbs over top.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 350°.

title: bread in a bag(child-approved)
directions: (This was made by 1993 LLF Summer Campers.)

title: peggy's salsa
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Drop a few at a time in boiling water to loosen the peel.
Pick out with slotted ladle as skin burst open on each tomato.
Cool.
Peel and core tomatoes.
Dice and place in stockpot or largest pot available.
Dice peppers and onions and add to tomatoes.

title: simple chili
directions: Combine ground chuck and onion in heavy soup pot.
Cook over medium high heat until meat is lightly browned.
Add the chili powder, tomato sauce, water, and beans.
Continue cooking over medium heat for about 15 minutes, stirring often. Taste and adjust seasonings, if needed.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time and add molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a tumbler.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: beef roast and mushrooms
directions: Heat butter and oil in large saucepan.
Brown meat slowly on all sides.
Add water.
Cover tightly and cook on medium heat 1 hour.
Add chopped pepper, onions and mushrooms.
Add salt to taste.
Cook until tender about 1 hour longer.
May need to add more water.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Remove stems from mushrooms and chop. Put caps aside.
Cook sausage in skillet until brown.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towel.
Save 2 tablespoons drippings. Cook chopped stems in drippings for 10 minutes.
Remove skillet from heat; stir in sausage, cheese and bread crumbs.
Fill caps with this mixture.
Put in baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except Fritos and cheese.
Cover the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish with 1 cup of Fritos.
Layer in order half of chicken mixture, then 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat, ending with Fritos topped with cheese. Refrigerate overnight or at least for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes approximately 10 servings.
Serve with green salad and garlic toast.

title: baked fruit
directions: Place in large bowl to mix. Pour into large casserole bowl, cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together.
Add raw apples, sliced bananas or any fresh fruit.
More brown sugar may be added, if you like it sweeter.

title: german-style baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Fry bacon until crisp; reserve 2 tablespoons bacon grease in pan.
Crumble bacon; set aside. Saute onions in drippings until tender.
Combine all ingredients in 3-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: canning tomatoes(easy method)
directions: Pour boiling water over tomatoes and peel off skins.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Put 1/4 teaspoon salt in pint jars and 1 teaspoon salt in quart jars, leaving 1/2 to 1-inch headspace.
Put lids on tight and put on heated cookie sheet in 225° oven for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and let cool in oven.
Remove jars and cover with cloth vat of air.

title: oriental noodle salad
directions: Cook broccoli flowerets.
Place in metal steamer basket set over a pan of boiling water for 7 to 10 minutes until tender crisp.

title: layered cranberry salad
directions: Combine pudding and lemon Jell-O and dissolve in 2 cups of water.
Add lemon juice and chill until thickened.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Cube bread; place in casserole.
Pour melted butter over top. Combine and simmer for 10 minutes the tomato puree, salt and sugar; pour over bread.
Bake one-half hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: meatballs and mushroom gravy
directions: Mix hamburger with bread crumbs, salt and pepper, then roll into balls.
Brown meatballs in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup and cup of milk.
Simmer until well mixed.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Wash chicken pieces, pat dry and sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic and paprika.

Brown chicken in 4 tablespoons margarine. Place chicken in casserole dish. Use remaining margarine to saute mushrooms. Drain artichoke hearts and arrange in casserole with chicken, then add mushrooms.
Combine soup and bouillon, then add this to casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cold chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice and salt over chicken; toss.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Just before serving, add rest of ingredients to chicken.
Toss gently to combine all ingredients. Can be served on a large lettuce leaf.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, add sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk. Blend together and gradually add to sugar mixture the eggs, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat. Blend in butter and vanilla. Immediately pour into baked pie shell. Press plastic wrap onto filling. Chill pie thoroughly or at least 2 hours. Serve pie with sweetened whipped cream.

title: pickled asparagus
directions: *Takes 1 pound of asparagus for 1 quart.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Roll in ball; roll ball in potato chips.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients using enough buttermilk for desired consistency.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.

title: mayonnaise drop biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot!
Makes 6 to 8 according to tin size.

title: weight watchers shrimp spread
directions: Mash shrimp with fork; set aside.
Whip cream cheese together with mayonnaise, onion, horseradish and lemon juice; set aside. Fold in shrimp.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours (preferably overnight).
Sprinkle with paprika. Makes 2 meals.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Stir all together.
Let set up and pour over top of cream cheese gently.
Refrigerate.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Brown chops well.
Place on top of rice in baking dish.
Pour over soup.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot grease. (I always add a large spoon of lard to shortening to fry fish.)

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt until part of the mixture is fine as cornmeal and part resembles small peas in size.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, broth and poppy seed together and add chicken.
Put in large casserole.
Melt margarine; add to crushed crackers and put on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: date pudding cobbler
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and baking powder. Cut in butter until crumbly. Gradually add the milk, dates and nuts.

title: marinated chicken kabobs
directions: Cut peppers, onion and chicken into 1 inch chunks.
Stir dressing mix, juice and oil in large bowl.
Add chicken and vegetables; toss to coat.
Cover; refrigerate 3 hours.

title: transparent pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients in double boiler, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into 2 pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a bowl.
Make a well and pour eggs, oil and strawberries in center.
Mix gently until well mixed. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.
Use a toothpick inserted into middle to check.

title: country-style steak(easy)
directions: Pour Worcestershire sauce on browned meat.
Add pepper to taste.
Stir water into onion soup mix.
Add mushroom soup and pour mix over meat.
Simmer covered 45 minutes to 1 hour until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: joys cheesecake
directions: *Ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together in saucepan.
Add flour and salt. Add milk and margarine.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: creamy freezer pie
directions: Chill the evaporated milk in an ice cube tray until almost frozen at edges.
Put the ice cold milk in a large bowl.
Use cold beaters (chill in refrigerator) and beat the milk until fluffy. Add sugar and Kool-Aid.
Whip until stiff.
Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan or square baking pan with vanilla wafers. Fill with the milk mixture.
Freeze until firm (about 3-4 hours).

title: cherokee squaw bread
directions: Combine
all
ingredients; add enough flour to make the dough easy to handle.
Knead it smooth and roll out until your dough
is about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut this into portions about the size
of a
quart jar lid and make some slits in it.
Now cook
in
deep fat, just like doughnuts.
Delicious with honey when warm!

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly. Dough will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes. Yield:
5 dozen.

title: jerky
directions: Cut meat in 1/2-inch strips.
Marinate in soy sauce, catsup, garlic and onion salt for 1 hour.
Place on air circulating racks in oven.
Set oven at 145°.
Leave in oven 6 to 8 hours.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Take by teaspoons and roll into a ball, then roll ball in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
When you remove from oven, place a chocolate chip or candy in the middle of each cookie.
Makes approximately 80 cookies.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix dry jello and strawberries, set aside.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Oil 9 x 13-inch pan and line bottom with marshmallows.
Pour cake batter over.
Spoon strawberry mixture on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Ice with Cool Whip.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix until crumbly the oleo, brown sugar and flour.
Add walnuts.
Put this in cake pan and bake 20 minutes, stirring 3 times.
Bake at 350°.
Remove from oven (save 1/2 cup for topping).

title: cream of potato soup ii
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients; cook until cheese is melted.
This freezes well.

title: yummy apple crisp
directions: Slice 6 or 8 large peeled apples and place in 8 x 8-inch pan. Cut margarine and flour together until crumb like, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ranger joe cookies
directions: Sift together or just stir together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix together shortening, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients into sugar mixture, then stir in oatmeal, chopped nuts or coconut and wheat or corn flakes. Drop by teaspoonful 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet (I use Pam).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: lemonade pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine Cool Whip, lemonade and sweetened condensed milk, blending well.
Pour the mixture into the crust and chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: black and white brownies
directions: Grease the bottom of a 13x9x2 baking pan; set aside.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Stir in half of the white chocolate chips and all of the semisweet chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread the batter in prepared baking pan.
Bake at 350 for about 30 minutes or until center is set.
Sprinkle with remaining white chocolate chips and bake 1 more minute.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Mix all thoroughly.
Bake in greased 11 x 7-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes (or until golden brown) in 400° oven.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Combine flour, meal, sugar, salt and baking powder in bowl. Add egg and milk; stir just to moisten dry ingredients.
Add cracklings.
Bake in hot, well-greased shallow pan at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
(Omit salt and baking powder, if using self-rising flour).
Stir in milk, oil and vanilla until smooth. Spread in 9-inch
square baking pan.
Mix brown sugar and remaining cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over all and do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange honey glazed chicken
directions: Make sauce with orange juice, honey, mustard, cornstarch, garlic salt, basil and onion.
Roll chicken in Bisquick and brown in frying pan in vegetable oil; remove to baking pan.
Pour sauce over chicken and place in 350° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes. About every 10 minutes, baste chicken with sauce.
Bake uncovered.

title: roast quail
directions: Sprinkle quails inside and out with salt, pepper and flour. Begin frying in about 2 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Gradually add 3/4 stick margarine and fry until golden brown. Cover and cook on low heat for about 45 to 50 minutes. Remove lid and increase heat for about 5 minutes so that quail will be crisp.

title: summer delight
directions: Add cream cheese and gelatin mixture to soup.
Add salad dressing.
Congeal.

title: zucchini chocolate chip bread
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Add zucchini and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured loaf pans (2) for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Top with confectioners sugar when cooling.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift the first 6 ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Add buttermilk.
Mix in raisins.
Shape into ball; knead for 15 seconds.
Make 7-inch round pad and 1 1/2 inches thick.
Score an X on the top.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 45 minutes.

title: punch buns
directions: Mix yeast,
water,
salt
and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients
and
then
enough
flour to make a soft dough.
Knead
thoroughly;
leave
dough slightly sticky.
Let rise until
double
in refrigerator.
Punch down.
This can be kept in
refrigerator
4 to 5 days.
Punch down each day.
Can be used
the
same day if refrigerated at least 2 hours.
This can be used
for dinner rolls, hamburger buns, sweet rolls or bread. Shape as desired.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Mix roast beef, water, cut up onion, salt and pepper in skillet.
Add flour to 1/2 cup water and mix well.
Add to roast beef to thicken.
Simmer until tender.
Serve over light bread.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of salted water for 10 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Combine next three ingredients in a skillet. Cook over low heat stirring constantly until cranberry sauce melts. Add carrots and stir gently.
Cook until heated.
6 servings.

title: banana peanut butter bread
directions: Slice
bananas into blender.
Puree until smooth (1 1/2 cups). Beat peanut
butter
and butter until smooth.
Beat in eggs, then bananas
until
blended.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually beat into
banana
mixture until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf
pan.
Bake
in
350° oven 50 minutes until wooden pick inserted
comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Turn onto wire
rack
to
complete cooling.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Combine sugars, eggs, oil and vanilla thoroughly.
Add sifted flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well with creamed mixture.
Add corn flakes, oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Blend. Drop from teaspoon or roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 15 dozen cookies.

title: green bean soup
directions: Make Low-Fat Ranch Dressing and add 1 to 2 cloves crushed garlic.

title: holiday pudding
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients, then add next 5 ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Raise heat to 400° for a few minutes at end.
Remove.
Combine pecans and butter; add to top.

title: frances' lasagna
directions: Brown meat, then add the next 3 ingredients.
Cover; cook for 40 minutes over low heat.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
In an 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan, layer half of the noodles.
Cover with 1/3 meat sauce, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 cottage cheese.
Repeat with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: norene's fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with bite size fruit.

title: monkey bars
directions: Beat together the first five ingredients, then add egg and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt emmy's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together in a large pot and simmer until thick, 3 to 4 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute butter, onions and celery.
Add bacon; fry and drain. Add flour and stir in milk, water, potatoes and white pepper.
Add cheese right before serving.

title: treasure cake
directions: Squeeze juice from orange and cut peel in sections, cutting out white lining.
Put raisins, nuts and orange peel through food grinder.
Add orange juice; mix and set aside.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and shortening on low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in all ingredients.
Spread in greased pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies pull away from the pan.
Cut into about 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: easy no fail caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine; remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar until smooth.
Return to heat and stir until boils.
Let boil 1 minute. Add milk and stir until it begins to boil.
Remove from heat and cool until you can touch bottom of pan.
Beat in confectioners sugar and flavoring.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and Jell-O together.
Add 1 1/2 cups hot water and mix well.
Let stand until it starts to jell, then add celery, pineapple and walnuts.
Refrigerate until it jells.
Serve with cream cheese mixed with mayonnaise or serve it without it.

title: pea salad
directions: Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
At serving time, drain.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with pineapple.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to an hour or until wooden pick inserted in middle comes out clean. Cool loaf in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.
Serve with cream cheese as an extra.

title: sweet rice
directions: Cook rice in water and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes over low heat.

title: ham and macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package. Drain macaroni and pour into casserole dish. Add cheese and ham; pour milk over mixture.
Put crushed crackers on top. Bake for 40 minutes.

title: cooked chocolate ice cream
directions: Put milk on to boil.
Mix flour and eggs together until smooth.
Add cocoa, that has been scalded with hot milk.
When milk boils, add flour mixture to it.
Cook until thick, remove from heat.
Add sugar
and part of canned milk, put in freezer can and add remaining milk, water and vanilla.

title: quick and easy carrot cake
directions: In small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, at medium speed, beat together oil, sugar and eggs until well blended.
At low speed, gradually beat reserved flour mixture into egg mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in carrots, pineapple with juice and pecans.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until cake tester inserted into center comes out clean (approximately 35 to 40 minutes).
Cool in pan on wire rack. Spread Creamy Frosting over top.
Refrigerate.

title: ranch style biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in dry ingredients and stir in buttermilk.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet. Let rise 15 to 20 minutes. Bake at 400° until brown (10 to 12 minutes).
Makes about 30 biscuits.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly. Add sugar, syrup and salt.
Mix well. Add melted butter and vanilla. Beat well.
Put chopped pecans in bottom of pie shell. Pour mixture over nuts. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; lower temperature to 300° and bake 35 minutes longer.

title: tomato pepper steak in crock pot
directions: Cut steak into 2
1/2 to 3 inch pieces.
Heat shortening in large skillet.
Coat steak with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown steak in shortening over medium heat (about 10-15 minutes).
Cut peppers and onions into large rings.
Layer meat, peppers, and onions in crock pot.
Cover with tomatoes and tomato juice.
Cook on low heat for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: oysterette snacks
directions: Place crackers in large self sealing plastic bag.
Pour in oil and turn from side to side until all crackers are moistened.
Mix dry ingredients together and pour into bag.
Seal tightly and turn from side to side until crackers are coated with seasonings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pastry for fried pies
directions: Cut shortening into flour. Add salt. Add milk and blend well. Usually you will need to add more flour to make dough workable.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Place
chicken	pieces	in
casserole
dish.
Mix soup, mushrooms, sherry and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice and salad.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour and oats, then flour and then nuts. Add raisins and nuts, if desired. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mash potatoes very well.
Add sugar, butter, vanilla, allspice, flour, milk and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Pat into pan and bake in slow oven until very brown.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: two ingredient muffins
directions: Beat 2 ingredients until smooth, then spoon into thoroughly greased muffin tins each about 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add 2 tablespoons of the 2 cups of	flour.	Beat
well.
Add
eggs	one at a time.	Beat well. Add
flour	and flavoring.	Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: zenobia bryant's sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually add milk and beat
until
well
blended.
Pour
into 9-inch pastry shell. Bake at 425°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake about 60	minutes.
Let
cool
and
garnish with nuts, if desired.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix together flour, 1/2 cup of the brown sugar and margarine to fine particles.
Press into bottom of pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients (except coconut) until just blended.
Add coconut and pour over bottom layer.
Return to oven and bake until golden brown.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Chop up artichoke hearts, garlic and steamed spinach.
Add all ingredients into a bowl and mix until well incorporated.
Pour into an 8 x 8 casserole dish.
Bake at 350 for 20-30 minutes; once the top is browned, remove from oven.
Serve with crackers, baguette style bread or sliced french bread.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Combine with soup, pepper and 1/2 can onions. Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Garnish with mixture of remaining onions and pimentos.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: pink stuff
directions: Sprinkle jello mix over cottage cheese and mix well.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple chunks and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: chow mein noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1/2 hour at 325°.
Put 1/2 can of noodles on top and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: hard soap
directions: Put on in an iron or porcelain kettle.
Let warm after lye has been added and dissolved.
Put in grease and boil until real thick.
Empty into mold at once. Let stand covered 24 hours.
Cut out.
Does not hurt to freeze this soap.

title: portofino (cranberry) salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple and wine.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Fold in pecans and pour into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until firm (overnight).

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Cream together with a pinch of tenderness.
Add 1 cup of faith, hope and charity.
Beat very lightly in a bowl of patience. Be sure to add a spoonful of gaiety that sings and also the ability to laugh at little things.
Bake in a good-natured pan. Cut in large slices and serve repeatedly.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients all at one time and mix.
Do not overbeat.
Batter should be lumpy.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 3 (8-inch) cake pans at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brown caramel filling
directions: Mix all ingredients together in heavy saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
(Stir constantly; otherwise it will scorch.)
When done, set aside.
Brown 1/2 cup sugar in heavy skillet over medium heat, and add to the first mixture.
Stir until cool.
Enough to ice 3-layer cake.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Good with chips or fresh vegetable pieces.

title: french iced coffee
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot coffee.
Cool.
Add other ingredients. Pour into ice cube trays and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Mix and serve.
Very icy.

title: fish salad(fish mold)
directions: Soften gelatin in hot water.
Oil mold and chill.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and store in an airtight container.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook together for 10 minutes or until thick the butter, dates and sugar. Cool and stir for a few minutes. Add cereal and nuts. Shape into balls the size of large marbles. Use confectioners sugar to coat the balls until white. Roll in large bowl or shake in bag.

title: hot appetizer pie
directions: Blend first five ingredients, then stir in dried beef and sour cream.
Pour into shallow baking dish and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.
Serves 8.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix pecans and coconut together and spread on bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Spread cake mixture over nuts and coconut mixture.

title: superb crab spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Beat until creamy, using an electric mixer or food processor.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.
Yields 2 cups.

title: potato delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a
large
bowl.	Pour into a 9 x 13-inch
pan
or
broiler pan.
Cover with topping and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown
beef,
onion
and
pepper in greased frying pan. Add tomatoes,
salt
and soup.
Simmer while cooking noodles. Add drained
noodles to meat mixture and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour into casserole
dish.
Add
cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Serves 4 or 5.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Grease an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Add undrained pineapple.
Add blueberries.
Add 3/4 cup sugar.
Add dry cake mix.
Add melted margarine and pecans with 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take spoon and punch down to crunch in several places. Cook about 20 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: dangood pie
directions: Stir together the sugar, pineapple, eggs, flour and coconut. Melt butter and combine with other ingredients.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350° or until filling is set and brown.

title: crock-pot dinner
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Put beef in crock-pot. Brown onions.
Add to beef in crock-pot.
Stir in all other ingredients and cover.
Cook 4 to 6 hours on low heat.

title: harvest pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken in large stockpot and cover with water.
Cook until chicken is done.
Remove from liquid, let cool and debone.

title: imperial lemon squares
directions: Blend first 4
ingredients
in	mixer.	Spread	in
9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Brown bacon in large skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Saute 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer on low until hot.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Serves 6.

title: cup, a-cup, a-cup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° until golden bubbly.

title: strawberry french pastry
directions: Place 2/3 of the box of crushed wafers in large baking dish. Cook eggs, butter and powdered sugar to thick cream consistency. Cook to 200° in double boiler.
Pour over wafers and cool.
Spread 1 cup whipped cream over mixture; next, spread 1/2 cup pecans. Next add both packages of strawberries, next 1 cup of whipped cream.
Top with remaining wafers and pecans.
Freezes beautifully.

title: a wonderful plain cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar; add extract.
Add 2 whole eggs and 1/3 of flour; blend well.
Add 2 more eggs and 1/3 of flour; blend well.
Add remaining eggs and rest of flour and blend well. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spanish skillet rice
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Add more water, if it becomes dry before the rice is cooked.
Toss before serving. Use an electric frying pan to cook the Spanish rice in and you can control the simmering heat better.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs, pumpkin and cream.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Turn oven down to 350°. Bake 50 or 60 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix salmon, cream cheese and green onions in mixing bowl.
Add lemon juice and garlic powder to taste.
Mix well.
Chill several hours before serving, or make day before.
Before serving, form into ball and roll in minced parsley.
Chill until ready to use. Serve with crackers.

title: crab fondue
directions: Combine crab with ingredients.
Heat until well blended.
Salt, pepper and Bay seasonings to taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: casserole supreme
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Add green pepper, onion and celery; saute until tender.
Remove from heat and add next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: triple onion baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400 degrees for one hour or until tender. Meanwhile in large skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp.
Remove to paper towels.
Drain, reserving one tbsp. of drippings.
Saute onions until tender and set aside.
When potatoes are cool enough to handle, cut in half lengthwise, scoop out pulp leaving an 1/8 in. shell.
In a mixing bowl beat the pulp, sour cream, and milk until creamy.
Stir in sauteed onions, american cheese and 1 c. bacon.

Spoon into potatoes shells. Place on baking sheet and bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese, green onions and remaining bacon. Bake 5-10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Yields 8 servings.

title: breakfast-in-a-pan
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover bottom of pan with cubed bread.
Layer with half the ham and half the cheese; repeat layers.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together in bowl. Pour over layers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil. Chill overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil. Bake for 30 minutes longer.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: my sister's swiss steak
directions: Pound steak with flour, salt & pepper to taste, and cut into serving size pieces. Brown.

title: chicken ben-bari(3 to 4 servings)
directions: Saute chicken pieces in the olive oil until browned on both sides.
Add the olives, celery, cloves, scallions, parsley and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper and coriander.
Stir well so the vegetables are evenly mixed with the chicken.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Transfer the chicken and vegetables into an ovenproof baking dish.
Mix together the wine and orange juice.
Pour over the chicken.
Peel the oranges and slice very thin; place on top of the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no cook fudge
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and cocoa and heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and mix until smooth.
Press into 11 x 14-inch pan.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: san francisco cocktail
directions: Chill the port; add the rum and lemon juice; mix well. Place in a glass container and refrigerate. When ready to serve, place a cherry or fresh strawberry in each glass, stir the cocktail well and serve very cold in wine or martini glasses. You may add a little ice to the shaker to keep it cold. Serves 12 - 16.

title: chicken like seasoning
directions: Blend all in blender except parsley until very fine.
Add parsley.

title: party dream salad
directions: Combine cheese, sour cream, lemon juice and salt.
Fold in fruit, nuts and whipped cream. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart mold and chill several hours.

title: pay day cake
directions: Cook syrup, butter and peanut butter chips on low heat until smooth.
Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Mix and pour over cake and marshmallows.

title: refrigerator vegetable salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, peppers and celery seed until sugar is dissolved.
Mix in drained vegetables.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all these ingredients together (mixture will be thick). Spread into well-greased long and deep cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and slice into bars.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In microwave oven combine ingredients in 1-quart glass bowl. Cook on High 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring after each minute.

title: puppy chow cereal snack
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth and creamy.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Pour cereal in a large bowl and pour melted mixture over cereal.
Stir to coat all cereal.

title: cheese garlic rolls
directions: In a large bowl mix Bisquick, milk and cheese; sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
Mix well with spoon.
Drop by tablespoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Melt butter and mix with garlic powder.
Brush on rolls while warm.

title: old fashioned cocoa cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients at high speed for 3 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with water to creamed mixture. Blend just until combined; add candy.
Pour into 2 greased and cocoa-dusted 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook onions, carrots and cauliflower for 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in milk and cook until thickened.
Add cheese (3/4 cup) to sauce and heat until melted.
Put vegetables in 1 1/2-quart to 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: springtime salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package instructions; drain. Combine pepperoni, zucchini, cucumber, tomato, radishes and carrots.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup chilled "Dill Salad Dressing" (recipe for dressing in cookbook).
Mix well.
Chill thoroughly. Toss salad before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: posole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Add onion, garlic salt, ground meat, cumin and oregano. Saut over medium heat until meat is thoroughly cooked and the onions are lightly browned. Add hominy; cover skillet and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve in bowls with topping of choice such as sour cream, guacamole or tortilla strips. Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt into a large bowl. Stir in the apples, nuts, butter and lightly beaten eggs.
Mix ingredients thoroughly together.
The batter will be very thick.
Transfer to greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until cake springs back at touch, about 1 1/4 hours.
Serve warm topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip bread in mixture and cook on both sides until slightly brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan cook cocoa, sugar and milk for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on buttered cookie sheets or wax paper.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef.
Blend all ingredients together in a slow cooker. Cook on low overnight.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to directions.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain peaches (saving 4 tablespoons of juice); arrange the peaches on top of cake.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice together.
Drop by teaspoonful on top of peaches. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Mix cinnamon and Cool Whip together and serve on warm or cool cake.

title: chi-chi dango
directions: Mix Mochiko, sugar and baking powder.
Add coconut milk and water (little at a time to avoid lumps).
Mix well.
Add vanilla. Add food coloring.
Pour into greased (using Crisco shortening, not oil) 9 x 13-inch aluminum pan (not glass).
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool completely.
Cut and roll each in starch.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Rub onto the pot roast.
In a skillet, brown roast in oil.
Place in a roasting pan.
Add water, onion, green pepper and seasoning.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done. Remove and keep warm.
Discard bay leaves.
Make thickening of flour and water.
Mix well and add to pan juice.
Cook and stir until thick.
Serve gravy with roast. Serves 8 to 10.

title: oatmeal raisin nut cookies
directions: Combine ingredients. Spoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, spices, onion and beans.
Crumble bacon on top.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken
breasts and shred.
Mix together shredded chicken, soups, rice
and water in 2-quart casserole dish. Add celery and	onions.
Pour
melted margarine over rice mixture. Cover and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: beef italiano
directions: Brown beef, onion and seasonings.
Add soup and water.
Pour over noodles in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chops supreme(jimmy stewart's favorite recipe)
directions: Boil 1 cup rice and place to one side.
Brown the 4 pork chops; add the celery and onion to the grease in the pan.
Brown this mixture.
Place chops in a casserole; put a mound of cooked rice over each chop.
Over this sprinkle the browned celery and onion.
Cover the entire mixture with the tomato puree and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until barely done; drain.
Add all ingredients, marinate and chill.

title: deep fried burritos
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in burrito mix with 1/2 cup water.
Add chopped onion and refried beans.
Simmer until heated through.
Fill shell with beef and bean mixture.
Top with taco sauce and cheeses.
Roll up shell with ends tucked in.
Fry both sides until golden brown.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.
Makes about 5 to 6 depending on size.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and mix with celery, onion and rice in a large bowl. Blend soup, milk, mayonnaise, salt and lemon juice and mix with chicken.
Mix well, then spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crushed corn flake crumbs and bake 50 to 60 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: cheese balls
directions: At room temperature, work all ingredients into a ball.
Roll in chips of green parsley and nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix with sugar, flour and buttermilk. Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cherry cola mold
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir into cheese mixture, blending well. Drain cherries and pineapple, measuring 1 1/2 cups of syrup.
Add syrup and cola beverage to jello.
Chill until very thick.
Fold in cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Blend in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm and serve.
If storing longer than 4 to 6 hours, wrap the pie to prevent dehydration.

title: sweet and sour chicken("for the wok")
directions: Mix together egg, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, sherry, sesame oil and salt.
Add chicken, stir.
Refrigerate one-half hour.
Dissolve 2 tablespoons cornstarch in vinegar.
Mix together with chicken broth, pineapple juice, sugar, ketchup and soy sauce.
Set aside.

title: chocolate almond torte
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt the chocolate with the butter.
Mix in the sugar with a whisk, followed by the eggs, almonds, vanilla and almond extracts. Spray an 8-inch layer pan with spray shortening; line the bottom of the pan with parchment or wax paper.
Spray with more shortening and dust with flour.
Turn the batter into the prepared pan and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack for 20 minutes.
Turn cake out of pan and peel off paper. Finish cooling.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts in a large container.
Combine sugar, butter and syrup in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat (stirring constantly).
Boil 10 to 15 minutes (stirring occasionally) or until mixture turns a light caramel color.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and nuts.
Mix to coat well.
Spread to dry.
Break apart.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Boil zucchini, onions and carrots for 5 minutes.
Drain and return to pan.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Add pepper to taste.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Use toothpick to test for doneness.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease an 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine dry ingredients. Stir in milk, oil and egg.
Mix just until moistened. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: never-fail popovers
directions: Mix with spoon; disregard lumps. Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Put in cold oven set at 350°.
Turn on heat.
Bake 35 minutes.
Do not peek!

title: cajun dressing
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in little oleo.
Cook sausage until done.
Drain grease out of sausage good.
Put all in pot with rice.
Cok down until done.
If too dry, add just a little more chicken broth.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Add water to orange rind and juice and shortening to make 3/4 cup.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg slightly; add to the liquids.
Then add to dry ingredients; stir well.
Add cranberries last.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 70 minutes.

title: french bread pizza
directions: Brown hamburger (or sausage, if you prefer).
Add all the other ingredients to suit your own taste.
Simmer together about 10 minutes.
Spread on sliced French bread that has been slightly toasted.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese and then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° until cheese is melted.

title: italian spaghetti sauce(cooked in microwave)
directions: Mix ground
beef
and onion in a 3 quart casserole with lid. Microwave
on High (100%) until beef loses pink color, 5 to 9 minutes,
stirring
times
to break up beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients;
cover.

title: beary best sugar cookies
directions: Mush dry ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, cream oil, margarine, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix both mixtures together in a large bowl.
No need to refrigerate dough or roll it out; just drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets, or roll by hand into 1-inch balls and flatten on cookie sheets using a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Invert one of the pie shells on waxed paper and allow to thaw. Prepare frozen vegetables per directions on package.
In another pan, mix chicken, soups, milk and potatoes.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is smooth and warm.
Mix in the vegetables and place in the frozen pie shell.
Carefully remove the thawed pie shell from its pan and fit to the top of the filling for a top crust. Put one or 2 slits in the top crust and bake at 350°
for about 25 to 30 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown.

title: punch
directions: Have
all
ingredients thoroughly chilled.
Just before serving, open and pour in punch bowl.
Stir well to mix.

title: chiles rellenos
directions: Rinse seeds
from
chiles
and dry on paper towel.
Cut Monterey Jack
cheese
into
1/2-inch
cube by 3 1/4-inch long strips.
Insert strip of cheese in each chile.
Beat eggs, add flour until
smooth.
Add
other ingredients and beat.
(I put all these in
the blender.) Place 1/2 of stuffed chiles in 7 x 13-inch pan.
Cover
with 1/2 of grated Cheddar.
Repeat these layers. Pour
egg
mixture
on
top over all chiles.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
(I have done part of bake time in the microwave.) Allow
10 minutes set time before serving, if possible.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Beat brown sugar, oil, egg, vanilla and sour milk.
Add rhubarb and nuts.
Mix in flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Stir until moistened.
Sprinkle with topping made of 2 teaspoons melted oleo, 2/3 cup of white sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 18.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream sugar and oleo in bowl. Add egg, then add yeast mixture.
Stir in flour with mixer.
Store, covered tightly, in refrigerator at least 8 hours.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Mash bananas.
Add pineapple, sugar and butter.
Crush wafers. Spread 1/2 on bottom of 8 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple mixture over crumbs.
Add remaining wafer crumbs.
Cover with nuts.
Let chill in refrigerator for at least 3 hours.
Cut in squares. Garnish with Cool Whip and cherries.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine sugars, flour, salt and eggs in top of double boiler; mix well.
Slowly add while stirring the milk and butter or margarine.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thick. Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into baked pie shell.
When cold, top with whipped cream and sprinkle with chocolate chips.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Place over boiling water and cook, stirring constantly for 13 to 15 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in Cheddar and American cheese and pimento.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with foil.
Grease foil.
Spoon mixture evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
