Cover with foil for last 15 minutes.
Let stand in pan until cool.
Remove from pan.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Yield:

title: ice coffee
directions: Place ice cream in a high glass.
Pour coffee and top with Cool Whip.
Serve with straw and spoon.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water together until temperature of 248° is reached or to the firm ball stage.
Pour the hot syrup slowly into well-beaten egg whites, while beating constantly.
Add vanilla and continue beating until the frosting will hold its shape when tossed over the back of a spoon.

title: zucchini with rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook zucchini in boiling water 5 minutes.
Cut lengthwise.
Scoop out centers and dice.
Add to the diced zucchini the other ingredients, all except the cheese. Lightly salt the zucchini shells.
Fill shells with zucchini mixture.
Place in greased baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Melt butter and saute curry powder, apple and onion. Add soup and cream.
In a shallow buttered baking pan lay chicken in one layer. Salt and paprika well.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and blueberries.
Save juice.
Dissolve jello in 1
cup boiling water, then add water to juice to make 1 3/4 cups.
Put into jello.
When using frozen berries, don't thaw. Add
berries
and
pineapple.
Let stand until jello is thickened. Stir.
Put
in
13 x 9-inch dish.	Top after jello is firm.
Stir sour
cream,
cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Beat well.	Spread over jello.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Boil together brown sugar, water, shortening, raisins, nutmeg and cinnamon.
When cool, add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake in square or loaf pan at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger tortilla pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder, tomato sauce and corn.
Arrange in layers in a flat casserole dish.
Starting with tortilla chips, add layer of beef mixture, olives, cheese and repeat, ending with cheese.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes or microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes. This is a good take-along dish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add marinara sauce. Cook spaghetti; drain and return to pot. Add margarine. Whisk eggs in a small bowl; add spaghetti. Divide noodles among two 9 x 13 inch dishes sprayed with Pam. Spread half carton of cottage cheese on top of each pie. Divide meat sauce equally and spread on cottage cheese layer (I use my hands to spread cottage cheese and meat sauce.) Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle mozzarella (or Vege Shreds) on each pie. Bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts. Yield: 2 pies, 6 servings in each pie.

title: peanut butter twirls
directions: Add enough milk to sugar, vanilla and peanut butter to make for easy handling.
This will be a very small amount.
Roll out in long rectangle shape not too thin.
Roll as in jelly roll fashion. Chill until firm.
Slice as desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to the degree on Tater Tot bag. Cook your ground beef. When cooked, drain fat. Add corn and cream of mushroom soup. Heat until warm.

title: tossed salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Top with your favorite dressing.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack 30 minutes.
Over low heat, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until blended after each.
Stir in flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased baking dish and top with chocolate chips.
Check for doneness with a toothpick.

title: cherry burst frozen pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla. Mix until well blended.

title: chocolate peanut butter snowman cake
directions: Cream sugar and peanut butter together; add all but flour, carrot and chocolate.
Fold in flour.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour in round cake tins.
After they cool, trim 1-inch around the top one and put the full size one under it.
Take the trimmings and cut a top hat out of it.
Frost it with Chocolate Peanut Butter Frosting.
Put coconut on it for snow.
Use end of carrot for nose and chocolate drops for eyes and mouth.

title: lew's ginger cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat together.
Sift together soda, flour, ginger and cinnamon.
Stir by hand.
Refrigerate at least a couple of hours (can be made ahead and refrigerated overnight).
Roll into balls (3/4-inch). Roll in granulated sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart (will spread out) 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.
Great with apple cider!

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed for 15 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Stir in drained cherries.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Immediately remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Garnish top of bread with cherries and sliced candied pineapple if desired.

title: baked barbecued chicken
directions: In
a little oleo, saute diced onion until soft. Add the remaining ingredients (except chicken) to onion and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Place chicken in a roasting pan or broiler pan and pour liquid mixture over all. Cover.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done. This is excellent served with mashed potatoes, as the sauce is delicious as a gravy.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Rinse the fish inside and out.
Cut all the fish across into 2-inch chunks.
Put the heads and tails into a pot; add water to cover and bring to boil. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: venison sour cream gravy
directions: Cover meat with vinegar and water.
Add sliced onions, salt and mixed spices.
Let stand overnight.
Place bacon strips over top of roast and bake at low temperature (275°) until meat is tender.
Cut meat into slices.
Use juices and thicken slightly with flour and water.
Add cream and meat to gravy.
Boil for few minutes to blend and serve with dumplings.

title: pepperoni rigatoni bake
directions: Heat large covered saucepot of salted water to boiling over high heat. Add rigatoni and cook as label directs.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a greased hot pan (or iron skillet). Bake at 400° until golden brown for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan spread pie filling over bottom of cake.
Put pineapple over filling.
Add dry cake mix, then spread coconut and pecans over mix.
Melt oleo and pour evenly over top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chef's pastry
directions: Cut butter into flour and salt mixture.
Add sour cream and store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: banana caramel pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars until light and fluffy; mix dry ingredients together and add alternately to the creamed mixture with 1/2 cup milk. Add vanilla. Mash banana and add to cake mixture. Chop nuts and fold in. Bake in a large tube pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: worthy - starter
directions: Place ingredients in glass container with loose fitting lid. Stir three or four times first day.
At end of two weeks, add 1 cup pineapple, chopped and 1 cup granulated sugar.
Stir every two or three days.
At the end of two weeks, add 1 cup peaches and 1 cup granulated sugar.
Stir every two to three days.
Two weeks later add 1 cup chopped cherries and 1 cup granulated sugar.
Stir every two to three days.
Let stand for two weeks.
At the end of the eighth week the addition of fruits should be started again, adding every two weeks.
Do not let starter get below three cups.

title: appetizer
directions: Chill sourdough rolls; slice and spread with butter.
Mix all other ingredients and set aside.
Place rolls on cookie sheet and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 250°.
Spread mix on rolls, then broil.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender (about 25 minutes).
Cool, peel and grate.
In a large pan, heat 1/4 cup butter with soup.
Blend in cheese and sour cream.
Stir in potatoes.
Place in 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Mix crumbs and 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Soften margarine and cheese at room temperature.
Then cream together.
Gradually add plain flour.
Add cayenne pepper to suit your taste.
Form into the shape you want or use a pastry bag and tube for desired shape.
On a cookie sheet, bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: salmon stew
directions: Mix together in large saucepan first 4 ingredients.
Bring to just before boiling (never boil).
Debone salmon; remove black skin.
Chunk and add to hot milk mixture.
Stir continually as milk will scorch.
Remove from heat; cover with lid.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with saltine crackers.
A family favorite especially on a cold night.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well, shape into a ball and roll in chopped walnuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: french bread
directions: Butter bread.
Sprinkle other ingredients on and broil lightly.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Coat a heavy saucepan with oil; add onions and cook over medium heat, stirring often, until onions are softened.
Add garlic and rice, stirring to coat rice with oil.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes, or until rice is opaque.
Add water, lentils, salt and pepper.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Boil water.
Wash eggplant and split lengthwise.
Place eggplant (face down) in boiling water.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove eggplant from water and let it cool, face up.
Add ground beef to skillet with a little water and cover; scramble periodically.
When water is absorbed and ground beef is frying, add onions and garlic.
Mix well.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Combine eggs, sugar and flour. Stir in chocolate mixture.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: makes its own crust cheesecake
directions: Mix well.
Pour over center of cheesecake; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Heat together vinegar, syrup, sugar, dry mustard, salt and paprika.
Cool mixture.
Then beat vegetable oil slowly into mixture with a whisk or blender.
Add poppy seed.
Serve as dressing over salad.

title: easy chicken main dish
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in butter.
Mix together all ingredients, including the sauteed mixture, in saucepan or crock-pot.
Cook on low heat until hot.
Pour over spaghetti noodles.

title: glazed peanuts
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan; cook over low heat until thick syrup.
Spread on cookie sheet; roast at 250° for 30 to 45 minutes or until peanuts are roasted as you like them.
Separate the peanuts if they stick together.

title: texas spicy shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and marinate for 1 to 2 hours. Grill for 4 minutes per side.

title: best ever potato soup
directions: Place first 9 ingredients in pot and bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer until vegetables are tender. Mix 1/4 cup milk with flour to make paste; stir into soup. Add remaining milk and cheese. Cook over medium heat until cheese is melted. Do not boil.

title: red christmas punch
directions: Add water to orange juice and lemonade according to package directions.
Dissolve Jello in hot water as directed on package. Place cinnamon stick in Jello and hot water.
Mix all ingredients. Punch can be served hot or cold.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and add both sugars, salt, soda and then eggs. Mix flour with chopped fruit and nuts.
Add the fruit mixture to batter, then add brandy and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon (very small amount) on greased cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 20 to 25 minutes (do not brown).
Can use 2 pounds of mixed chopped fruit.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake white cake according to package directions.
When cake is cooled, punch holes in cake, using a fork and set to the side.

title: easy hot fudge sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in top of a double boiler (put chocolate and margarine in after mixing the liquids and sugar together).
Let set over simmering water, can set for an indefinite time.
Stir occasionally.
The last step is to beat briefly.
This makes it lose its curdly look and leaves it smooth and finished.
Makes close to a quart of sauce.
Store in refrigerator.
May be heated in microwave or in jar set in water and heated, stirring occasionally.

title: meringue chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Spray cookie sheet. Drop by teaspoon.
Cook at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini squash soup
directions: Cut vegetables up small and boil until soft with the bouillon cubes.
Drain vegetables and save the liquid.
Put vegetables in blender (with enough liquid).
Return vegetables to liquid.
Stir and add as much milk as you'd like.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Heat and serve.

title: pancakes
directions: Note:
Need frying pan, fork, large bowl, spatula, cups and paper towels.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Combine the Karo syrup and sugar in a heavy pan over medium heat.
Stir constantly until it boils.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; mix.
Slowly add and mix in Rice Krispies.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy after school dumplings
directions: Take the can of cream of chicken soup and spoon it out into a mid-size pot.
Take the can that the cream of chicken soup was in and fill it with water.
Add the can of water to the chicken soup, then heat on high until boiling.
Take the can of biscuits and cut them in small squares.
When soup is boiling, you add the squared biscuits.
Heat them until they float to the top.
Reduce heat to a little over half and stir.
Optional:
You may add chicken bouillon cubes to make the soup richer.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix margarine, cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup sugar for the crust. Set aside.

title: grandma b's homemade cereal
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients. Add enough oatmeal to make it stiff and crumbly, about 1 pound. Grease large cookie sheet; spread oatmeal mixture on it. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Stir frequently. Bake until the mixture is brown through and through. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: death by chocolate dessert
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan according to the directions on the box.
Cool. Prepare pudding according to directions on the box.
Break cake into small pieces and layer one-half of the cake in a very large bowl. Spread half of the pudding on the cake. Spread half of the Cool Whip on the cake.
Shave the chocolate bar and sprinkle half on the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine cake mix, water, eggs, oil, nuts, pineapple, cinnamon and carrots in large bowl.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: creamy vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, mix soup, milk and vegetables.
Over medium heat, heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large
bowl,
combine
all ingredients and mix well. Roll in loaf and place in well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.	Serves 4 to 6.

title: low-calorie mayonnaise
directions: Combine ingredients in food processor or blender or beat with blending fork at high speed until mixture is light and smooth. Taste; adjust seasoning.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 3/4 cups mayonnaise.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend flour, margarine and powdered sugar together; press in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cherry filling over top. Sprinkle cake mix (dry) over mixture.
Cut butter over top, then sprinkle nuts over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine ingredients in an electric blender.
Mix until smooth and thick.
This makes as much as a 14 ounce can condensed milk at a fraction of the cost.

title: rice and tomato casserole
directions: Put raw rice in bottom of buttered casserole.
Top with tomatoes.
Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Mix with olives and salt and pour over tomatoes.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook rice.
Add pineapple, sugar, coconut and marshmallows together.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to cake type.
Add nuts; bake in an 8-inch pan.
Remove from pan.
Spread mixture of butter, creme de menthe and powdered sugar on top of brownies, then ice with fudge icing.

title: beefy spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until the meat is browned; drain.
Stir in the next 8 ingredients, except tomato paste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes, or until the rice is tender. Stir in tomato paste and heat through.
Serve with French bread. Serves 4 to 6.

title: seafood supreme
directions: Gently combine all ingredients.
Turn into a glass casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: paul lynde's stew
directions: Drain all vegetables except tomatoes.
Add all ingredients in 5-quart covered pan.
Bake at 250° for 6 to 7 hours.
If at all possible, try not to look during cooking time as it will turn out much better.
Makes its own gravy.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: easy and delicious filipino fruit salad
directions: You can buy the bottle of macapuno and sweetened sugar palm at the Oriental section of Star Super Market, Times or Safeway.

title: chili beans
directions: Wash beans.
Soak overnight in 2 quarts water.
Bring to boil. Simmer until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook until all are done.
Delicious with Mexican corn bread.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy in large mixer bowl. Mix on lowest speed.
Shape dough into balls with teaspoon.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie with a candy kiss. Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edges.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in 2 c. boiling water; add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple, mashed bananas and pecans.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into pan.
Chill.
Spread evenly with sour cream.
Pour remaining jello mixture on top. Chill & serve.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Cream the cheese with the sugar. Beat in egg and dash of salt. Stir in chocolate pieces. Set aside. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Fill paper baking cups (lined muffin pans) 2/3 full. Drop 1 teaspoonful cheese mixture into each cupcake. Bake according to package directions. Makes about 30 cupcakes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream softened margarine, butter and cream cheese together until smooth.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour; mix well.
Stir in flavoring.

title: blueberry and cream cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs and cream cheese until light and fluffy; add cake mix and oil and mix well.
Add water; mix well.
Fold in berries gently.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 16 servings.

title: grandma's ice cream
directions: Mix in 3-quart saucepan, condensed milk, egg yolks, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Cook until hot, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour milk mixture into ice cream freezer; add beaten egg whites and sugar.
Follow ice cream freezer directions for freezing.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Bake at 350° for 6 hours, stirring every hour or so.
Mash with potato masher after about 4 hours.
Serve on buns.

title: frozen parfait
directions: Boil sugar and water without stirring.
Form a thread, about 5 minutes (233° on thermometer).
Beat egg whites while candy is boiling.
Add salt to egg whites.
Slowly pour hot syrup into egg whites.
Beat until thick with mixer.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Whip the cream and fold in.
Layer with strawberries and freeze until ready to serve.

title: pork chops and potato bake
directions: Brown chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside.

title: dave's favorite pineapple cake
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix by hand.
Cook in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.
Cool in pan and top with icing.

title: cracker candy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line an 11 x 15-inch baking sheet with aluminum foil. Lightly spray with Pam. Completely cover bottom of the pan with crackers. Melt the butter and brown sugar together. Allow mixture to boil for 3 minutes. Pour over crackers and spread to cover all the crackers. Mixture will seep through and around all the crackers. Place in the oven for 5 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle the chocolate chips on top. Allow the chips to melt and then spread the chocolate around to cover the entire mixture. Add chopped nuts to the top and gently press down to make sure they stick in the chocolate. You can cut into squares or allow to cool completely and break into pieces like toffee.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Work butter in mix.
Beat egg; add milk and stir dry ingredients.
Spread dough in a well-buttered biscuit pan.
Spread apples on dough, pressing sharp edges of fruit into mixture.
Sprinkle with currants, sugar and cinnamon which has been mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix rice, shrimp and vegetables.
Mix salt, lemon juice, French dressing and mayonnaise.
Pour over the shrimp and vegetables.
Mix lightly.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice and set
aside.
In hot wok put olive oil and meat. Shake on
Accent
and
stir-fry
until done and lightly browned. Add rest
of
ingredients
and season to taste.
Add rice and soy sauce as
much
as desired and toss.
One may add cornstarch thickening
if
desired.
Vegetables
should be hot through and crunchy.
Use Pompeian olive oil.

title: ground beef and hot sausage casserole
directions: Saute meat in skillet.
Place in well-greased casserole dish. Arrange the remaining ingredients in layers in order given. Season each layer to taste.
Cover with juice or soup; add water to cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 5.

title: russian black bread
directions: Heat water, molasses, oil, sugar, salt, seeds and caramel color until very warm, hot (120°).
Add to dry ingredients and mix very well (I use Kitchen Aid Mixer).
Slowly add enough rye flour and mix until dough no longer sticks to fingers.
Let rise only 20 to 30 minutes.
Divide into 2 rounds on greased sheet pans that have been sprinkled with cornmeal.
Brush tops with oil and slash tops with sharp knife.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Heat soup in 1 1/2 cups water.
Melt cream cheese in soup
mixture.
Add gelatin and beat well until dissolved.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into oiled 6-quart mold and chill 24 hours.
Serves 30 people as a party spread.

title: new year's day dip
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, put black-eyed peas (you may use leftover ones) that have been mashed.
Layer onions, salsa and cheeses.
(This works better in a shallow dish.) Place in a 350° preheated oven for 25 minutes.
Serve at room temperature with chips.

title: paradise salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package.
Whip in cream cheese until smooth. Gently fold in all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: venison
directions: Marinate venison in 2 tablespoons vinegar and water to cover for several hours or overnight.
Drain venison.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 10 to 12 hours with mixture listed.

title: cheese-sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: french fried onions
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk and egg. Separate the onion into rings.
Let chill in ice water 15 to 20 minutes, then dip in batter. Fry a small amount at a time in deep fat at 375°.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Melt chocolate and butter on low heat.
Add to eggs/sugar mixture.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Test with knife for doneness.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown burger meat and sausage.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except Velveeta).
Add cheese slowly (cut in cubes). Place one spoonful of mixture on each rye round.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in plastic bag and return to freezer.
When wanted, remove and bake 10 minutes at 350° and serve hot.

title: mom's on strike casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Add noodles, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer until noodles are done, then add soup.
Continue simmering until done.

title: french beef stew
directions: In large Dutch oven over medium heat, fry bacon until crisp; push to one side of pan.
Add stew meat to pan and brown.
Stir in one cup water, wine, bouillon cube, garlic, instant onion, salt and thyme.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour until meat is fork-tender.
In covered saucepan over high heat in 1 inch of boiling water, cook onions ten minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Cook five minutes more and drain.
In bowl mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water.
Stir into stew.
Heat to boiling, stirring until thickened. Add onions, mushrooms, peas and olives.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until peas are tender.
Serve over rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pasta vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and top with dressing.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13 oblong pan.

title: nonfat whipped cream
directions: Beat until stiff or about 10 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar (after begins to get stiff).

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
all ingredients well and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Mix green peppers, chiles, sugar and vinegar and bring to rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.
Add pectin and 4 or 5 drops food coloring.
Mix well. Strain into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 6 (half pints).

title: cheesy beer ham soup
directions: In a quart pan, combine potatoes and onion.
Add the 2 cups water; bring to boiling.
Cover; cook for about 20 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in undrained corn, beer, mushrooms, parsley and dried mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Blend cold water into flour; stir into hot vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cheeses and ham.
Continue heating and stirring until cheese melts.

title: almond poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and milk in medium size bowl. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Beat in egg mixture.
Stir in poppy seed and almond extract. Spread in pans and bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Glaze (optional). Makes 2 loaves.

title: peggie's egg nog
directions: Combine milk, half and half and sugar until ingredients dissolve.
Separate eggs and beat yolks well.
Using low speed on electric mixer, add brandy very, very slowly to yolks.
In same manner, add rum and bourbon.
Add milk-sugar mixture to yolk mixture.
Beat egg whites until they hold soft peaks.
Beat cream until it is firm, but not too stiff.
Fold cream into liquor mixture, then fold in egg whites.
Grate small amount nutmeg. Chill overnight.
Stir or shake before serving.

title: skillet beef and noodles
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, brown beef with mushrooms, onion and garlic, breaking up beef with a fork, five minutes or until onion is hot.
Add tomatoes with juice, wine and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in noodles.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 25 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2 tablespoons cheese; sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: oatmeal cookies with pudding mix
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Shape into balls.
Place about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets and flatten by pressing down with fork or bottom of a glass.
Bake.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Butter 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cranberries over bottom of plate.
Sprinkle with sugar and walnuts.
In a bowl, beat eggs well; add 1 cup sugar gradually until thoroughly mixed.
Add flour, salt, melted butter and shortening.
Beat well.
Pour mixture over cranberries.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: western beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole. In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Add tomato sauce, garlic powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper; blend well.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Spoon corn evenly over meat mixture.
In medium saucepan, combine water, oleo and 1/2 teaspoon salt; bring to a boil (rolling).
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and potato flakes with fork until desired consistency.
To adjust consistency of potatoes, stir in a few more flakes for stiffer potatoes or a little more milk for creamier potatoes.
Stir in green chilies.
Spread potato mixture evenly over corn.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly around edges.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Top with tomato.
Makes 6 servings.

title: korean barbecued beef("bul kogi")
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces or into narrow strips, about 1/4 x 4-inches, always cutting strips across the grain for tenderness.

title: peanut butter crunch ball
directions: Melt margarine and pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Add powdered sugar and then the rest of the ingredients.
This will get hard, but mix real good.
Make into balls.
Let stand while you make mixture for dipping.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Note:
Using three pounds of veal gives more gravy if you steam it longer.

title: electric frypan stir-fry
directions: Brown hamburg, salt, pepper and pinch of garlic (if desired). Add cooked veggies and noodles.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Ready to eat when cheese is melted and slightly brown (if desired).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly
cream shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg. Sift
dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla.
Chill.
Roll
dough
into
walnut-size
balls. Place about
inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not hard.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: ambrosia
directions: Blend sour cream, coconut and marshmallows; mix well.
Drain juices off fruit and set aside (juices).
Cut peaches and pineapple into large chunks.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour fruit cocktail in with other ingredients and mix well.
Use about 1/3 cup of cocktail or peach juice or both and blend well.
Chill 1 hour or more before serving.

title: butterscotch nut bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Combine butterscotch chips, corn syrup, margarine and water in heavy saucepan.
Heat and stir over medium heat until smooth.
Stir in nuts; spread over crust.
Bake again at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, spiced and food coloring in pan.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat; add 3 Tbsp. margarine.
Sift dry ingredients; cut in margarine till mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once and stir until flour is moistened. On lightly floured surface, roll about 1/4 inch thick into 18 x 12 inch rectangle.
Cut into 6 inch squares.
Place whole apple in each square.
Sprinkle each apple generously with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot with margarine.
Moisten edges of squares.
Fold in corners to center and pinch edges together.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased 12 x 8 x 1 1/2 inch baking pan.
Pour the syrup over dumplings; sprinkle with sugar and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until apples are done.
Serve warm with whipped or ice cream. Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: In a medium bowl, combine spinach, cottage cheese, garlic powder, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Stuff mixture equally into noodles.
Place side by side in small baking dish. Cover with spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine and pour into eggs.
Beat this and add cottage cheese.
Add cornbread mix, broccoli and onion.
Pour into a greased skillet and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This can be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan instead of a skillet.
Freezes well.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Stir together in large container just until mixed.
Batter may be stored in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: cherry cream torte
directions: Brush ladyfingers with juice and place a layer around the sides and bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk and add all other ingredients. Add cheese to top and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Good with Triscuits.

title: the girl's favorite quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie shell.
beat eggs slightly.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour egg mixture into pie plate.
Cook, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300°.
Cook, uncovered, until knife inserted in middle comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, beating briefly.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Alternately add the flour mixture (flour, baking powder and salt) with the milk, mixing gently.
Beat egg whites to soft peak, then gently fold them into the batter.

title: hot macaroni salad
directions: Blend flour with drippings from bacon.
Add sugar and salt. Slowly add liquid part of recipe and stir until thickened. Crumble bacon and add rest of ingredients.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Boil sugar, milk and oleo 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove and add chocolate, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts. Stir until melted.
Set for 10 minutes.
Drop on wax paper.
Spoon hurriedly before it sets.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil and add to dry Jell-O. Allow to cool
but not to set.
Mix cream cheese with milk and then add to Cool Whip. Stir into pineapple mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: crepes souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Cook in buttered pan until golden brown.
Serve with syrup.
May have with strawberries and cream or whatever you like on top.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pare potatoes; cut in quarters. Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper into bag. Moisten potatoes with water and shake in bag, coating well with mixture.
Place a layer of potatoes in pan.
Turn once; sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 to 1 hour or until done.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Place potatoes in a large bowl, add cold water to cover. Let stand for 25 minutes. Preheat oven to 425°. Spray a nonstick baking sheet with vegetable cooking spray. Set aside.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift cake flour.
Measure; add 3/4 cup sugar and sift 5 times. Set aside.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until egg whites stand in a peak, not dry.
Add vanilla and almond flavoring.
Then turn the mixer on low speed and add 1 cup sugar.
Add 1/3 at a time with mixer on low just until mixed.
Then add flour and sugar that has been sifted together (do this by hand with a wire spoon).
Use about 1/3 of flour and sugar at a time and fold it in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple, cheese, flour and sugar. Stir well. Pour into casserole dish. Mix crackers with margarine. Spread over pineapple mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the beef and onion; simmer with bay leaves.
Cook 8 wide noodles.
Drain.
Arrange all the rest of ingredients in layers in this order:
noodles, pizza cheese, Muenster cheese, sauce, Romano cheese and cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Put through
food
chopper
enough cucumbers to make 16 cups. Also 4
bunches
celery,
green	peppers,
2 red hot peppers and 6
large
onions.
In saucepan, put 1 gallon vinegar, 6 pounds brown
sugar
and
cup
salt.	Use 2 ounces mustard seed in cheesecloth
bag.
Add 2 pounds cornstarch to thicken vinegar. Add all the vegetables and cook slowly until done.	Seal while hot.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together the ground beef, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes, tomato paste and water; simmer for 45 minutes.
Mix together the eggs, cottage cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes and Parmesan cheese.
Place in layers: noodles, cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and cheese over rice
directions: Place cooked rice on plate and add cubed ham of desired amount.
Microwave until warm, about 2 minutes on High (100%). Place desired amount of cheese on top of ham and microwave until cheese is melted, about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately, letting each individual salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Combine the sugar and pineapple; add eggs and oil, beating very well. Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Blend into the first mixture. Add vanilla. Pour into a buttered 13 1/2 x 10 greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done. Ice while hot.

title: tortures (french meat pie)
directions: Place meat, onions, seasonings and water in Dutch oven or heavy kettle.
Cook meat without frying on top of stove.
Stir constantly for first few minutes.
When meat is fully cooked, remove from heat and strain.
Let the liquid cool and the fat come to the top. Remove most of the fat.
You can do this after it becomes solid and cold.
Return the balance of the liquid to the meat.

title: european carrot cake
directions: Combine the squeezed orange and lemon juice in a measuring cup and add enough salad oil to make 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Pour into a bowl and add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Sift the dry ingredients into the oil mixture; add the chopped nuts and carrots.
Blend well.
Pour into a lightly greased tube pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Bake a little longer if cake does not feel firm.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.
A rich nutritious cake for children and snack time.

title: mint patties
directions: Add sugar to cheese gradually until mixture does not stick to hands.
Add peppermint oil a drop at a time.
Flavor to taste. Flatten into small patties and dip in chocolate.
Necessary chocolate can be purchased at craft or candy shops.

title: crab meat imperial
directions: Melt butter. Saute onions and pepper.
Mix flour and milk in double boiler until thick and smooth.
Add ingredients.
Grease dish.
Put in crab meat and pour ingredients over top.
Sprinkle cheese and cracker crumbs over top. Bake.

title: braided sweet bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, margarine and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, beaten eggs and half the flour. Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff but sticky dough.
Cover and let rise until doubled.

title: orange floats
directions: Whirl orange juice concentrate, yogurt and milk in a blender until smooth.
Pour into tall glasses.
Top each with a scoop of sherbet.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 2 or more hours before serving.

title: steak diane
directions: Sprinkle steaks with lemon pepper seasoning.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add margarine.
Place over medium heat until margarine melts.
Add steaks and cook 5 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.
Transfer to 9-inch platter; keep warm.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard to skillet; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Pour over steaks.
Garnish if desired and serve immediately. Yields 6 servings.
Contains 179 calories (41% from fat) per 1 steak and 1 1/2 teaspoons sauce.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add chicken broth, soups and chicken.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Grease casserole dish lightly and spread tortillas on the bottom and the sides.
Spoon in chicken mixture to cover tortillas well.
Sprinkle with cheese; dot with Ro-Tel tomatoes and sprinkle chili powder over tomato layer.
Alternate layers and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package; cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate refrigerator cake
directions: In top of double boiler pan, melt marshmallows and broken candy bars with milk.
Stir occasionally to make a smooth texture; set aside to cool.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and butter.
Place 2/3 crumb mixture in bottom of an 8-inch square pan. Reserve rest to sprinkle on top.
Whip cream.
Fold into pudding mixture and pour into crust-lined pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top. Chill 4 hours.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Spread dessert topping on bottom of crust.
Pour milk into large bowl, adding pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and chopped toffee bars. Spoon into crust.
Garnish top with pieces of chopped toffee. Freeze 4 hours or until set.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain the pineapple, saving 3 tablespoons of the juice.
Combine flour, sugar and juice.
Add the cheese and pineapple; stir well.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine the butter and crushed crackers and spread on top of the pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix well all the ingredients, except can of beef gravy.
Roll into balls.
Brown well in frying pan.
Add a can of gravy and cook slowly in pan or oven for 1/2 hour.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Mix sauerkraut with the sour cream.
Put in greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Crumble the corned beef on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top of corned beef.
Dice the 6 slices of dark bread and cover the cheese.
Drizzle 1 stick oleo over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sour cream dressing for fresh fruit salad
directions: In medium saucepan, combine the eggs, sugar and juices.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in sour cream thoroughly.
Pour over fresh fruit salad.

title: pumpkin roll(serves 12 slices)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spray medium jelly roll pan with Pam.
Spread mixture on pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn over onto wax paper and aluminum foil.
Roll in wax paper only and cool about 45 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a bowl in the microwave until melted (5 to
6 minutes).
You must stir them to see if they are soft. They do not lose their shape.
Fold in cream cheese and powdered sugar until mixed.
Add nuts if desired and then in a buttered pan, spread it out and refrigerate 20 minutes.
Cut and put on a plate.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add buttermilk mixture, eggs and shortening to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Pour batter into 9-inch cast-iron skillet (or pan).
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: frosted carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, wheat germ, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, oil and carrots.
Beat at low speed, then high speed until well mixed. Stir in walnuts. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread in hot water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Then squeeze out moisture.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Form small balls, about 20.
Brown slowly in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add to sauce and cook 30 minutes more.

title: frosted lime walnut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until partly set. Stir in 1 can of pineapple, cottage cheese, celery, pimento and walnuts.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Frost with cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice mixed together.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares.
Serve on green salad lettuce.

title: easy brownies
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Cook pudding according to directions.
Put cake mix in mixing bowl and mix in cooked pudding for 2 minutes. Spread mixture out on a greased and floured cookie sheet (13 x 9 x 1-inches).
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let cool totally and cut into bars.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes, carrots and celery in water 20 minutes. Drain.
Reserve liquid. Saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk. Stir constantly until thick. Add vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more liquid until right consistency.

title: creamy chicken soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour.
Stir in chicken broth, milk and cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened and boiling.
Add chicken and pepper; return to a boil.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken until tender in well-seasoned water.
Remove chicken and broth, measure 1-quart broth back into pan.
Bone and dice chicken.
Set aside.
Into broth put celery, green pepper, onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Let cook a few minutes.
Then add spaghetti and cook until spaghetti is done.
Add tomatoes, olives, soup, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add Worcestershire sauce and cheese to boned chicken, then add to spaghetti mixture.
(I use half sharp Cheddar and half Velveeta.)
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mushroom-pork casserole
directions: Stir-fry pork in combination of olive oil and salad oil (2 tablespoons) until pork looks pink.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic and saute about 3 to 5 minutes in total.
Prepare rice in chicken broth.
In casserole mix the ingredients with cheese, egg and enough broth to moisten.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup and milk.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce.
Top with butter.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer, or until potatoes are brown.

title: texas trash
directions: In large bowl, combine pretzels and Chex Mix.
Set aside.
In 1 cup measure, combine butter, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, garlic salt and red pepper sauce.
Microwave at High for 45 to 60 seconds or until butter melts.
Stir.
Pour over Chex mix and pretzels, tossing to coat.
Microwave at High 3 to 5 minutes or until mixture is hot and butter is absorbed, stirring after each minute.
Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: beef noodle zap
directions: Throw all ingredients into microwave-safe bowl with lid, except parsley.
Zap on High 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle parsley over top.

title: sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix flour and sugar.
Heat butter, cocoa, water and shortening in a pan to boiling point. Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, baking soda, eggs, vanilla, and cinnamon; mix well.
Pour into 11x20 inch or equivalent pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 400 degrees for 18 minutes.

title: stuffed snow peas
directions: Trim ends from pea pods.
Bring 3 cups water to boil. Carefully lower pea pods into water.
Simmer over medium heat 1 minute.
Drain.
Immediately immerse in cold water.
Drain and refrigerate until chilled.
Chop beef fine.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Slice slit on one side of pea pod; fill with mixture and arrange in dish with sides touching to keep from falling. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve cold.
Makes 60.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn bread according to box directions.
Add corn.
Brown ground beef with onion in skillet.
Pour off grease.
In a pan larger than 9 x 13-inches, layer half of corn bread mix, hamburger mix, Cheddar cheese, picante sauce and the rest of the corn bread mix.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix
and
bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 little pies or 2 big pies.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Mix with butter, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add cinnamon and milk.
Beat mixture well.
Place in pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: swiss dip
directions: Cut the Swiss cheese in chunks and add rest of ingredients. Heat and serve on cocktail rye bread.

title: chicken fance
directions: Remove skin from chicken; wash and drain well.
Melt butter with garlic, salt and pepper in medium size pan.
Mix potato chips and corn flakes in pie pan.
Dip pieces one at a time in melted butter mix, then in crumbs, coating well.
Arrange in single layer in large shallow baking pan.
Remove garlic from butter and pour remaining over chicken.
Bake in moderate oven for one hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Fry onions and cabbage until cabbage is tender.
Brown hamburger meat.
Add tomato paste and hamburger meat to mixture. Simmer approximately 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: johnny with hamburger
directions: Put in baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken fayette
directions: The sauce is designed for 4 servings.

title: deli ham sandwich
directions: Remove rolls from pan; split crosswise, making 2 layers. Place ham and cheese on split rolls and replace tops.
Mix margarine, mustard and poppy seed; spread over tops of rolls. Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes, or until tops are browned.
Great for small brunch.

title: crunchy pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: bourbon franks
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 1 hour in crock-pot over low heat.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in one bowl, then mix wet ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour wet ingredients into dry and stir just until mixed.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit treat
directions: Mix and press in cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together and cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 packages yeast to 1 cup lukewarm water.
Add yeast water, salt and eggs to first mixture.
Stir in flour with hand.
Put in greased bowl; grease top of dough and place in refrigerator overnight lightly covered.
Punch down dough once before morning.
Next morning, knead dough and pinch into small balls.
Place in greased pan and set for 3 hours.
Then bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in a big pot; pour off grease.
Add onions and green peppers.
Cook until browned a little.
Add chili seasoning, tomato paste, tomato soup and water from each can. Bring to a boil, lower heat.
Simmer on low until most of the water has boiled down.
Keep checking and stirring often.
Add kidney beans.
Cook for another 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot. Good with corn bread.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together and bake at least an hour until brown on top. Bake at 350°.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook
chicken,
covered,
on
low heat with onion until tender (2
to 2 1/2 hours).
When tender, add tomatoes, beans and
corn. Cook at low boil for 10 minutes.
Good served with lettuce
wedge salad, biscuits and butter, apple pie ala mode and milk.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill a 9 x 13-inch pan with apples.
Sweeten apples to taste and add cinnamon (1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon).
Mix ingredients and sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Cook pudding as per directions. Stir cake mix into hot pudding.
Mix well. Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips and walnuts. Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: raspberry topped lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until clear and thickened.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with condensed milk, lemon and food coloring.
Pour into crust and bake 30 minutes.
Spoon raspberry mixture evenly over top of pie.
Chill 4 hours.
Spread whipped cream over top.
Garnish as desired.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add egg and flavoring; mix thoroughly. Stir dry ingredients together and blend into sugar mixture. (Refrigerate if necessary to roll.)
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured cloth and cut with decorative cookie cutters. Place on sheet (lightly greased).
Bake 7 to 8 minutes until lightly golden brown in 375° oven.
This cookie is good for any occasion and little kids love them and big kids, too.

title: microwave cashew crunch
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and lightly butter.
In medium microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and add cashews until blended well. Microwave for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until mixture is light brown.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Microwave 1 more minute.
Add baking soda and stir quickly.
Spread onto cookie sheet, spreading mixture quickly with a wooden spoon.
Cool about 30 minutes and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add milk to corn;
add flour, sifted with salt, pepper and baking powder.
Add shortening and beat in eggs.
Beat well.
Fry by spoonful on griddle or frying pan.

title: pauline's cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Spread bean dip in casserole dish.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream.
Put on top of bean dip.
Top with chopped lettuce, tomatoes, grated cheese, jalapeno peppers and green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cornbread hushpuppies
directions: To this you can add 1 can corn or cauliflower or green onions or all three.
Mix well.
You want it stiff; add flour if necessary.
Drop by tablespoon in hot grease.
Drain and put on paper towel.

title: texas salad
directions: Can layer other vegetables if you like.

title: quick shrimp creole
directions: In a skillet, cook first 3 ingredients in butter over medium heat until tender (about 10 minutes).
Add combined flour, salt, sugar and file mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Stir to combine.
Add 3/4 cup water.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook rice; keep hot.
When onion mixture has cooked 15 minutes, add tomatoes and rest of ingredients (except rice).
Heat.

title: molasses ginger cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Add flour until able to hand make small balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl and bake in a loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit. Stir in pudding. Chill at least 30 minutes.

title: betty's chocolate chocolate chip muffins
directions: You will need 24 foil baking cups.

title: boiled broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli and
cut
thick
heads
into
1-inch long pieces.
Place thick end in boiling water and cook, uncovered, for 10 to 20
minutes.
Add
the
rest
of the broccoli to the boiling water and cook
5 to 10 more minutes.
Drain and serve with butter;
spread over the broccoli.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham ring-around
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease large cookie sheet. In large bowl, combine butter, parsley, onion, mustard, and lemon juice. Blend well. Add cheese, cooked broccoli and ham. Mix lightly. Set aside.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Boil noodles until tender, about 11 minutes.
Put 1 teaspoon cooking oil in water; drain noodles.
Brown hamburger; drain grease off.
Mix sauce and cottage cheese together.
Simmer and stir to blend.
Layer noodles and hamburger; pour over sauce. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's punch
directions: Mix fruit juices and sugar; chill at least 2 hours (better overnight).
Just before adding to punch bowl, add ginger ale and soda water.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up the broccoli (use only the tops).
Cut up the apricots in pieces (use scissors).
You can use cashew pieces or the 1/2 pieces.
Shake together the mayo, sugar and vinegar.
This is good on any vegetable salad.

title: scripture cakeapple raisin cake
directions: Follow	Numbers
11:8.	Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients
together.
Cream
butter
and	sugar.	Add egg to butter
mixture and mix.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix in apples and raisins by hand.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake approximately 90 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Finely crush vanilla wafers (but not to a powder).
Chop pecans into small pieces.
Melt butter.
Add all ingredients together and bake at 250° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: cherry sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and spices in medium saucepan.
Add apple juice, a little at a time to prevent lumps.
Add food coloring.
Cook over medium heat until mixture starts to boil and cook for 2 minutes more.
Stir in cherries and nuts; heat through. Serve warm over pork or poultry.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Bring these ingredients to a boil; cook 1 minute.
Add vanilla and set aside to cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until creamy.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat egg whites at room temperature, cream of tartar and salt at high speed of an electric mixer 1 minute.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in chopped pecans and vanilla.
Spoon meringue into a well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Using a spoon, shape meringue into a shell, swirling sides high.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Combine chocolate and water in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, until chocolate melts.
Cool; stir in brandy. Beat 1 cup whipping cream until stiff peaks form; fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into cooled meringue shell; chill at least 3 hours.
Beat remaining cup of whipping cream until stiff peaks form; spread evenly over top of pie.
This pie takes some time to make, but it is worth the effort.

title: microwave potato casserole
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes and onion.
Pour can of cream of mushroom soup over potatoes and onion.
Cook for 10 minutes. Rotate dish and cook for 5 to 10 minutes, until done.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix sugar and baking mix, cut in butter.
Mix in half and half and vanilla.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Pour fruit into a 7 x 11 inch pan and heat for 10 minutes.
Roll chilled dough out on floured surface.
Place over fruit.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden, brush with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add egg and almond extract; beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, beating well. Chill about 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in pecans.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press cherry half into center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields about 6 dozen.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in the other ingredients.
Spoon into a small ovenproof dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: baking powder
directions: Sift together 6 times.
Multiply the recipe as needed.
Store in covered container at room temperature.
Will keep up to 6 months.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Stir into cream.
Add pineapple.
Cook in double boiler until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.
Peel and dice apples.
Add nuts and cooled dressing.
Add cherries and mix.

title: filet mignon
directions: Combine first three ingredients in large Ziploc bag.
Add steaks.
Refrigerate 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove steaks from marinade.
Place on coated rack in shallow, roasting pan. Broil 6 inches from heat for 5 minutes each side.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain vegetables.
Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 of cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 of onions.
Pour in 1-quart casserole and bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Cook noodles and celery until done; drain. Add rest of the ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: wacky cake
directions: Make 2 round 8-inch cakes.
In a large bowl, place 1 cake on the bottom.
Place some pudding on the cake in bowl.
Next, cut up candy bar and sprinkle half of it on top of the pudding, then add Cool Whip.
Now do the same thing on the second layer only save the other half of the candy pieces for the very top of the cake.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until serving time.

title: red party punch
directions: Mix together chilled punch and juice; add last 2 ingredients. Just before serving, add sherbet by spooning into large punch bowl. Pineapple chunks may be added if desired.
Makes 2 large punch bowls.
Serves 24 to 30 people.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Spread cream cheese on tortillas.
Add slices of ham and hot peppers, then roll tortillas, chill and slice.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat; add sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Spoon batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle mini marshmallows on top while warm.
Frost with:

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.
Drizzle with orange glaze.

title: creamy leek dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: whipped butters
directions: In small bowl, beat butter at highest speed until light and fluffy.
Add one of the variation ingredients and beat until blended.
Great with English muffins for brunch.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients together to form dough.
Roll or pat dough out.
Cut shapes with cookie cutters.
Make hole for ribbon.
Air dry.
Turn over at least once.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger first, then drain.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour (or less, if you don't have time).
Cook spaghetti noodles, rinse and serve with sauce.

title: barbie's beach dessert
directions: Mix
2 c. of wafer crumbs and butter in 13x9-inch baking dish.
Press firmly in bottom and refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in bowl until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of cool whip.
Spread over crust.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl for 2 minutes until dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice to make 2 cups.
Stir into gelatin.
Refrigerate 5 minutes until gelatin is slightly thickened.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Add other 1/2 of cool whip and 1/2 c. crumbs.

title: chocolate, peanut butter, oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening until softened.
Add eggs and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add vanilla.
Stir in oats and chips.
Bake cookies at 350° for 15 minutes.
This is a big recipe.
Should yield at least 4 dozen cookies.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in usual way.
This makes 3 layers of cake.
Bake in 325° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken deluxe
directions: Cook and drain broccoli spears; arrange in bottom of casserole.
Add toasted almonds; cover with chicken chunks.
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, vinegar, vanilla and coconut.
Mix. Add margarine.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for one hour at 350°.

title: pound-a-pound-a-pound
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage in skillet.
Drain fat.
Add Velveeta.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pile on slices of bread. Serve hot.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Chop cabbage, onions and peppers. Cook 15 minutes using very little water. Add corn, sugar, salt, celery seed and vinegar.
Mustard moistened with vinegar should be added last.
Cook until corn is tender, about 30 minutes.
While hot, pack into jars and seal.

title: beef and pepper spaghetti
directions: Cut beef and green pepper into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Heat wok over high heat; add cooking oil.
Stir-fry the meat, half at a time, until browned.
Remove meat from wok.

title: parslied meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the catsup and cooking spray, in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf. Place loaf on a rack in a roasting pan coated with cooking spray. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Spread catsup evenly over meat loaf.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken or turkey casserole(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, place on top 1 1/2 cups breadcrumbs mixed with 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie crunch #1
directions: One can of Libby's pumpkin pie filling plus 2 eggs plus 2/3 cup evaporated milk can be substituted for the first 6 ingredients.

title: frosting for angel food cake
directions: Brown almonds in oven.
Brown coconut in oven when almonds are done.
Watch carefully.
Fold into whipped cream mixture and spread on angel food cake.

title: mexican layered casserole
directions: In a large greased casserole dish, place the following in layers:
Doritos, hamburger meat, onion, chili beans, grated cheese, cream of chicken soup, chopped tomatoes and green chilies and sour cream.
Sprinkle Doritos over top.
Place in oven at 350°. Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: turkey-vegetable stroganoff
directions: Bring hot water to boil in a large saucepot.
Heat oil in a large skillet over high heat.
Crumble in turkey and, stirring often to break up pieces, cook 5 minutes, until no longer pink. Meanwhile add noodles to water and boil 4 minutes until tender. Drain and spread on serving platter.
Cover and keep warm.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place pie crust in pan (see directions on box).
Bake for 9 minutes at 400°.
Saute onion in olive oil (or vegetable oil). Season chicken with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dice chicken and add to skillet.
Cook chicken until done, then drain.
Rinse broccoli in cold water until thawed; drain.
Mix soups together. In bottom of casserole dish, later chicken, broccoli, soup, then cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted (approximately 30 to 45 minutes).

title: garlic-parsley potatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Toss to coat well.
Layer half in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle half of parsley over, then remaining potatoes.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Uncover, sprinkle on remaining parsley and serve.
Serves 8.

title: mother's rolls
directions: In a large bowl dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, egg, milk and 3 cups flour.
Stir; let rest 10 minutes. Mix in enough of the remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out and knead until smooth, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch dough down. Turn out onto a surface and let rest for 5 minutes.
Grease muffin cups.
Divide into balls in each cup.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool to set.

title: southern fried pies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut shortening into mixture.
Add milk gradually, mixing into dry dough.
Roll out on board to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds the size of a saucer.
Place 1 tablespoon fruit in one half of each round, folding remaining half over fruit.
Moisten inner edge with cold water and press together with fork.
Brown in shallow fat, turning over until both sides are brown.

title: busy day hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain fat.
Combine soup and water, add salt and pepper; mix with meat.
Brown potatoes in skillet in 2 tablespoons oil.
Place potatoes in 2-quart casserole.
Lay meat on top.
Place cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (can be frozen).
Freeze without cheese.
Thaw, place cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deep dish chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour, bouillon and pepper.
Over medium heat, gradually add milk; cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients except biscuit mix; mix well.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Prepare biscuit mix according to package directions for rolled biscuits.
Roll out to cover dish; cut slashes in center of dough.
Place on top of dish; crimp edges.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and soft margarine together and spread in pan.
With wire whip, mix pudding and milk together until well blended.
Then spread on cracker mixture.
Put layer of bananas over pudding.
Put well drained pineapple over bananas.
Spread whipped topping over pineapple, making sure to seal edges well. Sprinkle nuts over topping and the cherries for decoration.
Let set in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Drop cabbage leaves in boiling salt water for few minutes. Drain, combine hamburger meat, onion, salt, pepper, rice and egg together.
Use 2 tablespoons of soup, roll meat in cabbage leaves. Secure with toothpick in skillet.
Pour rest of soup over cabbage rolls.
Simmer for 40 minutes or pressure cook for 10 minutes.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender, drain.
Put in a bowl and cut out the core.
Mash up real good.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix together, if too sticky add more flour. Heat oil in the skillet and drop the cauliflower by a teaspoon and brown on all sides.
Set on a paper towel to drain off excess oil.

title: hot german-style potato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet fry bacon until crisp. Remove, crumble and set aside.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add green pepper and cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in water, vinegar, sugar, cornstarch and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, until thickened.
Gently stir in potatoes, crumbled bacon and 1/2 can of onions.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes, until golden brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Pinch off small pieces of dough into balls (approximately 3/4-inch).
Place on baking sheet. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for approximately 15 minutes. Makes about 8 dozen.
They freeze well, too.

title: spoon bread
directions: Bring water and butter to boiling point; add salt and meal moistened with a little water.
Cook until thick.
Beat eggs; add baking powder and milk.
Add to first mixture.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Blend together in a blender all ingredients, except ice cream. Pour into punch bowl.
Add ice cream by large spoonfuls.
Stir until smooth and serve.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Mix cheese and onion. Spread thinly on large dinner plate with rim.
Spread half bottle of Heinz cocktail sauce over cheese mixture.
Drain 1 large can crabmeat plus 1/4 pound fresh crabmeat or mock crabmeat. Flake crabmeat and sprinkle over cocktail sauce. Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: tuna dip
directions: Soften gelatine in water.
Heat soup and cheese until softened.
Add gelatine and stir.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Chill overnight.
Serve on Ritz crackers.
This makes a lot.

title: roquefort, potato, and mushroom tart
directions: To prepare pastry, combine flour and salt. With fingertips or pastry blender, cut in the butter until crumbly. Add egg yolk and milk. Form pastry into 2 flat disks, one slightly larger than the other. Wrap each in plastic and refrigerate.

title: cherry dessert supreme
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well and press into the bottom of a 9 x 11-inch cake pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef tips in a skillet until browned.
Add onions and mushrooms and saute another 5 minutes.
Add water, salt, pepper, thyme, and garlic.

title: good cracker spread
directions: Place 5 eggs in boiler, cover with cool water, add 1 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil. Let boil for 15 minutes. Remove from heat, pouring off water.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt, cut in lard until pieces are like small peas.
Add water and gently toss with fork until moist. Form dough into ball, on lightly floured surface, flatten dough and roll out.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Add these ingredients to batter.
This make a huge amount. Can be baked into muffin or loaves and then frozen.
This is a great naturally sweet treat for lunches also.

title: vegetable and chip dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with raw veggies (carrots, cauliflower, broccoli) or chips.

title: enchiladas verde
directions: Place green pepper, lettuce and broth in food processor or blender.
Blend until smooth.
Heat oil and add green pepper mixture, salsa and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes, remove from heat and whisk in sour cream.

title: lucci's lentil macaroni soup
directions: Wash lentils in strainer; clean good.
Put under running water a little at a time.
Add remaining ingredients to lentils.
Cook all together.

title: vera griffey's beans
directions: Brown bacon, onion and ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Cook in crock-pot or 1 hour in a 350° oven in a 3-quart casserole.
Leftovers freeze well.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: beef-bean combo
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion in 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven until hamburger is light brown; drain.
Stir in green beans (with liquid) and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until noodles are tender, 25 to 30 minutes or cover and cook in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in a large microwave bowl.
Heat on High in microwave for 11 minutes, stopping after 3 1/2 minutes. Stir.
Restart; stop again after 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir; restart. Remove from microwave.
Add vanilla, marshmallows and peanut butter.
Mix well until dissolved.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: calico cheese soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Drain and set aside. Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan over medium heat until tender.
Reduce heat to low; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Combine milk and broth; gradually add to flour mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is slightly thickened.
Stir in 2 cups cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Add reserved vegetables and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Ladle soup into individual serving bowls. Garnish each serving with croutons and finely shredded cheese.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: In a saucepan, over medium heat, combine peanuts, sugar and water.
Cook.
Stir until mixture crystallizes and coats peanuts, about 10 minutes.
Spread in an 11 x 15-inch buttered cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and lift and turn them over and over.
Bake another 15 minutes and cool.
Makes 4 cups.

title: easiest swiss steak
