directions: Remove outside fat and cut steak into serving pieces. Sprinkle with salt.
Brown under broiler, turning once.
Remove from broiler and place in baking dish.
Stir onion, herbs and bay leaves into tomatoes.
Pour over steaks.
Cover; bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours, until beef is tender.
Stir flour into cold water to make smooth paste.
Pour over steaks; bake for 20 minutes more, or until sauce thickens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with a little cinnamon and sugar and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon white sugar.
Mix and redistribute in pan evenly.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over top of apples (do not stir).
Top with extra cinnamon if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Best warmed with whipped cream.

title: microwave chicken cacciatore(total cooking time:  34 to 40 minutes)
directions: In a 3-quart microproof casserole, combine onion, green pepper and butter.
Cook, covered, on High (Max power) for 4 to 5 minutes, or until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes and flour; stir until smooth.
Stir all remaining ingredients except chicken. Cook, covered, on High (Max power) for 5 minutes.
Add chicken pieces, immersing them in sauce.
Cook, covered, on High for 20 to 25 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Stir once during cooking. Allow to stand 5 minutes, covered.
Remove bay leaf before serving with cooked spaghetti or rice.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring ingredients to boil.
Put grape leaves in bottom of jars.
Put small pickles in jar.
Use head dill, dill seed and alum in each jar.
Pour mixture into jars.

title: blanche's lemon chess bars
directions: Sift together flour and sugar; cut in oleo.
Knead and pat into 8 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Pour lemon filling over hot pastry and continue baking for 25 minutes.

title: cherry-rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb in water until tender.
Add sugar and cook a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pie filling and cook 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together the eggs, milk, bread crumbs, 2 teaspoons salt, pepper, celery salt, sage and raisins; let stand 5 minutes.
Add meat and mix.
In large pan, saute onion in oil until crisp-tender.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stuff cored and halved peppers.
Place in sealed freezer bags for freezing.

title: what's it?
directions: Brown beef, onion, pepper and celery in skillet.
Drain if necessary.
Add cream of soup, stirring to blend.
Mix together cream cheese and sour cream.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Crumble angel food cake in medium pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, evaporated milk with mixer until creamy.
Add pecans and stir into mixture.
Pour mixture over angel food cake pieces.
Spread blueberry pie filling over mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: sour cream chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla. Mix together in a bowl the baking soda, flour and cocoa. Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately, blending well after each addition. Bake in preheated 350° oven approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick chocolate chip cookie sticks
directions: Mix sugars, oil, vanilla and egg until smooth.
Stir in flour, salt, nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well.

title: christmas pudding
directions: *I usually use equal amounts of raisins, golden raisins and currants.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix all cake ingredients together. Pour batter over nuts.
Bake 1 hour. Cool. Invert on serving plate.
Prick top; spoon and brush glaze evenly over top and sides.
Repeat until glaze is all used up.

title: crumb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as usual.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 11 x 17-inch or larger baking pan.
Spread batter in pan and bake 20 minutes.

title: fritos dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill. This dip is best with Fritos.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: confetti tuna in celery sticks
directions: In a small bowl, toss together tuna, cabbage, carrots and squash. Stir in cream cheese, yogurt and basil. Add salt and pepper to taste. With small spatula, spread mixture evenly onto celery sticks. Makes 10 to 12 servings. Calories: 32; Carbohydrate: 3g.

title: e-z fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips over boiling water.
Add Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and nuts.
Mix together.
Pour into a pan.
Cool down until firm.
Cut and enjoy.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat 2 minutes.
Take 3/4 mixture and pour into greased and flour tube pan. The rest of the mixture stir chocolate syrup into it.
Mix well.
Pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add squash, onion and bell pepper; cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Drain well. Stir in mayonnaise and next 5 ingredients; pour into a lightly greased deep 2-quart casserole. Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In an electric mixer bowl, mix together cake mix, instant pudding, oil and water.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Stir in sour cream, chocolate chips, pecans, grated chocolate and coconut.
Bake at 350° in well-greased Bundt or tube pan for about 55 minutes or until testing pick comes out clean.

title: butter fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla. Add flour, then nuts. Shape into ovals. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar when hot, again when cool.

title: pork chop skillet
directions: Flour pork chops on both sides.
Fry in oil until brown on both sides.
Remove pork chops and drain grease.
Put pork chops back into skillet and add potatoes, onion, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugars and eggs in a large bowl; beat until creamy, then add water, salt, soda, flour, vanilla and cinnamon and mix well.
Chill dough for at least 1 hour or let set overnight.
Roll out dough and cut into desired shapes.
Decorate with your choice of sprinkles or colored sugars.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for about 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour, milk and Karo.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in water.
Add butter and vanilla; beat well.
Nuts may be added.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend well.
Add well beaten egg yolks, beat until mixture is light and then add pineapple.
Do not drain off juice.
Sift flour together with baking powder and salt. Add to first mixture.
Then add vanilla and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Yields three 9-inch layers.

title: simple punch(for large punch bowl)
directions: In large punch bowl, add the ginger ale.
Float on top the sherbet.

title: layered jello salad
directions: Mix jello, strawberries and boiling water until dissolved. Add bananas and pineapple; mix.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into bowl and chill until set, but not firm.
Add vanilla yogurt to remaining jello mixture and pour over other layer.
Makes about 10 to 12 servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Beat egg yolks.
Mix with milk. Cook until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla.
Put in a baked pie crust and top with egg whites, beaten.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and whipping cream.
Mix well. Pour into can of ice cream freezer.
Add sweetened condensed milk and chocolate syrup; stir well.
Add milk to fill line of freezer. Freeze.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimientos and 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: swedish meatball stroganoff
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, eggs, milk, onion and spices.
Form into balls no more than 1-inch.
Brown well.
Place in Dutch oven.
Add beef broth and simmer 30 minutes.

title: fried beef with scrambled eggs(6 servings)
directions: Wash and clean the beef to cut into 0.3 cm thick.
Beat both sides with the blade of knife.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 tablespoon wine, 3 tablespoons water and 2 teaspoons cornstarch. Mix well.
Mix eggs with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon oil. Heat 5 tablespoons of oil in the pan.
Stir-fry the beef over very high heat for two minutes.
Remove from the high heat and add the egg mixture.
Mix evenly.
Sprinkle with chopped green onion.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Slice peppers and onions in half and then in even slices. Slice sausage diagonally in bite size slices.
Add all to large pot and add enough water to pot to steam everything.
Season to taste.
Cook until peppers are tender.

title: baked turkey
directions: Clean and wash turkey.
Put 1 teaspoon of salt in cavity of turkey.
Rub in and then stuff with celery stalks, onion and carrots.
Rub butter on outside of turkey.
Season with salt, pepper and season salt.
Put in and broil.
Bag it and bake it according to size of turkey.

title: chicken stew
directions: Brown bacon in margarine.
Remove bacon and set aside to cool.
Break up in bits for garnish over finished dish.
Cut up chicken into 1 inch chunks and brown in skillet about 10 minutes. Remove to bowl and cover.
Add onion and garlic to skillet, cook and stir until onion is soft about 3 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and chicken to pan.
Cover and simmer until veggies are soft.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together the broccoli, soup, mayonnaise, 1/2 of the cheese and
bread	crumbs.
Put
into
a
baking dish and cook until it gets
hot
through.
Remove
and top with cheese and bread crumbs. Cook
until
cheese
melts and bread crumbs are brown.
Cook at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Spread	green beans in casserole dish; spread soup over beans. Sprinkle grated cheese on top of soup.
Cover with lid or foil and
bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, then add onion rings and dabs of butter.
Broil, uncovered, 2 to 4 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In large bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
In small bowl, mix bananas, eggs, milk and oil.
Pour liquid into dry ingredients and mix well. Pour batter into pans and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes until bread pulls away from side of pan.
Poke with toothpick to check doneness.
If toothpick is clean, bread is done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix 2 sticks margarine, powdered sugar and eggs.
Beat at high speed for 15 minutes. Pour over crumbs.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with electric mixer.
Add flaked coconut.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Remove from oven and while still hot, poke holes into the cake with a meat fork.
Pour the can of cream of coconut over the hot cake and into the holes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Chill.

title: pink angel salad(good for parties and fast.)
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Makes a beautiful, delicate, very "rich" dessert.
You can serve it on a lettuce leaf as a salad with crackers or I usually serve it as a dessert and everyone likes it very much.
Let it set in refrigerator for about 1 hour before serving and enjoy!

title: fancy one skillet dinner
directions: In a large skillet with lid, cook hamburger until it loses its red color; break meat up with spoon as it cooks.
Stir in 5 cups boiling water, onion soup mix, bay leaf, pepper, mushrooms, tomato sauce and red wine.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Stir macaroni into boiling liquid; return to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and boil slowly, stirring frequently, 25 to 30 minutes, or until pasta is cooked through.
Add additional water, if needed.

title: chicken "la crab"
directions: Pound chicken breasts to flatten.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook onions and celery in 1/2 cup butter until transparent.
Remove from heat and add 6 tablespoons wine, the crab and stuffing mix; mix well.
Divide mixture among chicken breasts, placing in center of each piece.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Combine flour and paprika. Roll chicken in mixture to coat.
Divide between two 11 x 7-inch casseroles.
Drizzle remaining butter on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice; set aside.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic powder evenly over chicken.

title: five-layer macaroni salad with chicken
directions: Prepare salad as directed on package except stir catsup and relish into dressing.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes, chicken, cheese and macaroni salad in 1 3/4 or 2-quart glass bowl or square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg, if desired.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Heat butter and oil in oblong 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in a 400° oven until butter is melted.
Place chicken in dish, turning to coat with butter mixture.
Arrange chicken, skin side up, and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, flour and pineapple juice together.
Grease (butter) a casserole dish (1 1/2-quart size).
Place pineapple chunks in bottom of dish.
Pour mixture over chunks.
Put bread cubes on top and pour melted butter over bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn to 350° and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cover immediately.
Don't open and serve until next day.

title: oatmeal raisin nut cookies
directions: Combine and beat all ingredients on low speed until well blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove immediately from sheet and cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt the chips over hot, not boiling, water.
Stir in the peanuts and noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: western chex brittle
directions: Heat brown sugar, corn syrup, water and salt to 250° (hard-ball) in heavy 4-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add nuts. Continue cooking over low heat to 285° (brittle in cold water).
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix in soda and margarine.
Stir in Chex to coat all pieces.
Work quickly!
Spread on greased baking sheet.
Separate into thin layer with greased fork.
Cool.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: egg souffle
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch dish and chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a microwave-safe dish.
Do not stir!
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Stir.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Stir.
Pour in a square dish and chill until ready to serve.

title: beef-chip
directions: Cut dry beef in pieces.
Mix milk and flour together, then add beef, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Cut biscuit in half and serve sauce over it.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Heat marshmallows and margarine 2 1/2 minutes in microwave on High.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies to marshmallow mixture. Mash into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate bits in microwave 2 minutes on High or until hot.
Use to frost the treats by spreading on top.

title: french toast
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar and salt in a medium size bowl.
Dip bread slices individually into batter and brown in buttered skillet or on a griddle.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in corn meal. Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth, about 1 minute (do not overbeat). Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in hot oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 7-week bran muffins
directions: Soak bran flakes in boiling water and cool.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add Buds, buttermilk and water mixture.
Mix well with large spoon.
Makes 1 gallon.
Do not stir when baking, just dip out.
Will keep 7 weeks in refrigerator. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast and butter bread.
Put toast in a 9-inch cake pan. Cover toast with raisins.
Blend all other ingredients together. Pour over toast and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a knife stuck in the center comes out clean.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, salt and sliced onions 2 hours, covered with water.
Rinse.
Heat sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar to a boil.
Cool.
Add to cucumbers and onions.
Put in freezer.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Over low heat simmer for about 5 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add syrup, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw Tater Tots about 1 hour at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Melt margarine. Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake about 45 minutes or until heated all the way through and cheese is bubbling.

title: low calorie butterscotch pie
directions: Mix pudding with skim milk, then add Cool Whip. Stir until smooth.
Pour in pie crust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: london broil pinwheels
directions: Pound flank steak with meat mallet until 1/2-inch thick. Sprinkle with tenderizer, garlic and green onions.
Roll up, lengthwise, jelly-roll fashion.
Cut roll into 8 slices and spear each slice on a skewer.
Place skewers into a shallow dish.
Mix sherry, soy sauce and tomato paste until smooth; pour over meat. Turn skewers and marinate at room temperature for 2 hours.
Drain skewers and reserve marinade.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook on 375° to 400° until brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Add cheese until melted. Remove from heat. In a separate bowl mix sour cream, onions, salt and pepper. Add butter and cheese mixture, mix with frozen hash browns. Spread in casserole dish. slightly dot top with butter. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's peach cobbler
directions: Cut in shortening.
Add water, a little at a time.
Roll out on floured surface.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: chili taco salad
directions: In 2-quart salad bowl, layer hot chili, lettuce, olives and tomatoes.
Spoon guacamole over tomato.
Top with cheese and corn chips.
Serve immediately.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: sliced turkey and giblet gravy
directions: Bake turkey breast and slice.
Make gravy from soups, starch and eggs.

title: kahlua toasted almond
directions: Pour Kahlua, Amaretto and cream over ice.
Stir.
You can also use vanilla ice cream instead of milk or cream and blend for a smooth treat.
Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate shavings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the popcorn.

Remove the grains that did not pop. In iron skillet, put molasses and margarine. Stir constantly for about 10 to 12 minutes after it starts boiling. Add peanuts to the popcorn and mix. Pour cooked molasses over the popcorn and peanut mixture. Roll into balls and wrap in plastic wrap.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix melted margarine and sugar. Add eggs and other ingredients. Pour in pie shell and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: knock you out vodka sauce
directions: Do not add any salt.

title: yummy cornbread
directions: Heat oil in skillet and mix with all ingredients, leaving a small amount in skillet.
Pour mixture in skillet and cook at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package Jell-O in 3/4 cup hot water. Add 1 cup juice from oranges. Add water to make 1 cup if needed.
Pour into dish and add oranges.
Let congeal.
Heat milk and sugar. Dissolve the second box of Jell-O in 3/4 cup hot water.
Add to milk mixture.
Add sour cream.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over congealed Jell-O.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice the onions and enough cucumbers to fill a gallon jar. Mix the remaining ingredients; bring this to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Put in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in 2 weeks.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Brown the meat, then add onion, celery and green peppers. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Cut tortillas into bite-size pieces and line the bottom of a pan with them.
Combine together soups, tomatoes, chili powder, garlic powder and add to meat mixture.
Pour half the mixture over the tortillas and sprinkle with half the grated cheese.
Repeat with a second layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together flour, beer and sugar.
Pour into a greased 9 1/4 x 5 1/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Loosen bread from sides of pan.
Poke small holes on top of bread.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Mix 1 cup flour with 1 packet chicken stock; set aside. Season chicken with 1 packet of chicken stock and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour and set aside.
Heat oil, saute mushrooms and onions.
Remove from frying pan; set aside.
In jar, combine flour, 1 packet chicken stock and water; shake well.
Pour liquid in frying pan.
Return chicken, mushrooms and onions.
Heat until bubbling.
Remove from pan and place on warm platter.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: ice cream chocolate sauce
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together 1/3 cup of the water with the cocoa. In a medium-size heavy saucepan, heat the semi-sweet chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring often, 5 minutes or until melted. Whisk in the cocoa mixture, the remaining 1/3 cup of water, both sugars and the corn syrup and bring to a boil, uncovered, for 7 minutes or until the sauce is reduced to 1 1/2 cups. Remove from the heat and stir in the vanilla. Serve over ice cream.

title: fizzy punch
directions: In large mixing bowl or pitcher (3-quart), blend spices with pineapple juice.
Add remaining fruit juices and Pillsbury sweetener.
Chill.
Just before serving, add carbonated water.

title: sweet 'n low brownies
directions: In a small bowl, combine oleo and cocoa; set aside.
In another bowl, stir together flour, nuts, baking powder and salt.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch square pan with nonstick spray.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Beat in Sweet 'N Low, vanilla and extract. Beat in cocoa mixture.
Gently fold in flour mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Calories:
100 per serving.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, butter, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell. Bake until firm, about 50 minutes.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in mixing bowl all other ingredients except flour.
Now add yeast mixture and flour, beating well after each addition; cover.
Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size (about 1 hour).
Stir dough down.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch round casserole (1 1/2-quart).
Let rise in warm place and bake.
Then brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
Firmly shape into 6 patties.
Over medium-high heat, heat 10-inch skillet until very hot.
Add patties; cook 3 or 4 minutes on each side until browned.
Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and water.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes, or until meat is done, stirring occasionally.

title: broiled fish with tangy sweet & sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except cilantro & fish in a small saucepan; cook & stir over medium heat until mixture boils & thickens. Simmer 2 minutes. Add cilantro; mix well. Remove sauce from heat & keep warm. Place fish on lightly oiled baking sheet. Broil 4-6 inches from heat source 10 minutes per inch of thickness or until fish turns opaque & flakes easily when tested with a fork. Spread sauce over fish to serve.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Beat Egg Beaters and add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into a large cast-iron skillet that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press with back of floured fork to make crisscrosses.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: raisin molasses sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl cream together shortening and 1 cup of sugar. Add molasses and egg.
Beat until well blended.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt.
Stir into molasses mixture and mix well.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Slightly flatten with bottom of a glass if desired.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 1 minute.
Remove cookies to wire rack.
Cool.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: peach and cream cheese cake
directions: Mix well the first 8 ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 10-inch round pan.
Place sliced peaches over batter. Combine cream cheese, sugar, juice and vanilla extract; beat until smooth.
Spoon mixture to within 1 inch of edge of batter. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over cream cheese filling. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Filling will appear soft after cooling.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Add onion and celery and cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Put in 1/2 mixture, then layer 1/2 cheese.
Layer remaining mixture and they the other half of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: plantation chicken salad
directions: Add all ingredients except mayonnaise.
Moisten with mayonnaise and toss to mix.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf. Serves 6 to 8.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook yellow squash and onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Spread half of stuffing mix in 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Cover with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Drain.
Add melted butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook in oven until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Stir every minute.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of cabbage, white sauce and grated cheese.
Top with bread crumbs and paprika and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn dish 1/2 through baking time.
Serves 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato juice, tomato paste, seasonings and pepperoni.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Boil noodles while this thickens.
Drain and add cold water to noodles to prevent them from sticking together.
Drain again.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Mix caramels and milk in saucepan on stove, stirring until all the caramels melt.
Remove from heat and put on bottom of crust. Mix cream cheese and sugar with a little milk.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Bake in oven at 350° about 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
When cooled, put in refrigerator. Makes 8 servings.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together well.
Store in tightly covered container.
To serve, add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of mixture to a cup of boiling water.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add pecans and mix until all nuts are coated.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add nuts and coat thoroughly.
Place on buttered jelly roll pan or cookie sheet (I use Pam first).
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Yields 1 pound.
Good for munching anytime.

title: cape cod cranberry pie
directions: Put chopped nuts, cranberries and 1/2 cup sugar into buttered 10-inch pie plate or spring-form pan.

title: holiday cheese roll
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, garlic and pecans in large mixing bowl.
Blend until thoroughly mixed.
Form cheese mixture into rolls, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Sprinkle paprika on a sheet of waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Roll cheese rolls in paprika until completely covered.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill well in the refrigerator.
Slice thinly to serve.
Makes 2 cheese rolls, approximately 6 x 1 1/2-inches.

title: rudolph's antlers
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt chocolate and butterscotch pieces over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chow mein noodles.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto a waxed paper lined baking sheet, making "v" shaped cookies about 2 inches long. Place a cherry half in the center of each.
Chill in the refrigerator 1 to 2 hours or until firm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thickened. Make a meringue.
Brown until golden brown in a 325° oven.

title: pineapple chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Heat oil in skillet for 1 minute.
Add chicken and garlic.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce mixture and cook until bubbles and thickens.
Serve over rice.
Makes 2 large servings or 4 small.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pick meat off of bones.
Make up a box of chicken stuffing mix (saving out herb mix).
Put stuffing in bottom of casserole dish and lay chicken over this.
Mix together the two soups and herb mix.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine.
Mix eggs and sour cream or yogurt; add to onions.
Season with dash of Tabasco and pepper. Pour into pie shell; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then at 325° for 20 minutes more.

title: brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oleo and eggs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese, vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread into crust.
Chill.

title: russian cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and salt all together, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir all together and roll in hard ball by hand the size of walnuts.
Lay on cookie sheet; press down with spoon a little.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes and roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese slices in a large mixing bowl.
Mix lightly.
Place in a pan and shape into a loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Remove loaf from oven. Cut each cheese slice into 2 triangles and arrange, overlapping, on top of loaf.
Return meat to oven 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes prior to slicing.

title: italian sponge cake
directions: Separate egg whites and put in a large bowl.
Put yolks in small bowl. Beat whites first. Sift 1/2 cup sugar in slowly after the whites start to thicken.
Beat yolks with 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Pour yolks into white. Do not beat.
Fold in (turn spatula or wire whisk over and under).
Egg whites have to stay fluffy. With flour in sifter, sprinkle over batter and fold.
Pour batter into ungreased tube pan (line with wax paper).
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven. Remove from oven and invert pan immediately to cool.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin flavors separately, using 2 cups boiling water each for lime and raspberry gelatins and 1 cup boiling water for lemon gelatin.
Stir marshmallows into lemon gelatin; set aside.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water to lime gelatin and pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until set, but not firm.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Foil line a baking dish.
Layer pork chops first and then potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Then spread cream of mushroom soup on top.
Seal foil and bake for 45 minutes or until chops and potatoes are tender.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in salt water. Drain. Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass pan with Pam.
Layer sauce, noodles, spinach, cheese, noodles, sauce and cheese. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 375°.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Heat garlic bread and toss a salad while lasagne sets.

title: apple cake
directions: Add all dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Blend in apples, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Put into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: fried okra and tomatoes
directions: Fry okra (fold lightly while cooking, do not mash) until brown.
Drain well.
Drain tomatoes and crush.
Place okra back into the pan.
Pour tomatoes over top and cook about 10 minutes, stirring lightly.

title: chili con queso appetizer
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients.
Add rest and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Serve in fondue pot.
Great over tortilla chips.

title: candied potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut lengthwise into thin slices.
Melt margarine in a large iron skillet.
Stir in sugar.
Add sweet potatoes. Cover and cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Uncover; cook 5 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Transfer to serving dish. Sprinkle with walnuts.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and place in baking dish. Sprinkle Ritz crackers over top.
Melt butter and drizzle over casserole.	Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, corn flakes, onion, pepper and 1/4 of soup; mix well.
Form into meatballs the size of a small egg. Place in a baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Don't brown or fry the meat.
Mix rest of soup with milk and pour over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour; meatballs will brown nicely.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brownie cake
directions: Sift in bowl; sugar, flour and baking soda. In sauce pan; bring to a boil; butter, cocoa and water. Pour over flour mixture while boiling hot, mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured cookie sheet 12-15 min. Does well in deep cake pan.

title: west indies salad
directions: Mix and stir meat, onion, salt, pepper and oil.
Pour mixed vinegar and water over meat mixture.
Let marinate.

title: icebox fruit cake(the best)
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in milk in top of double boiler.
Crush graham crackers fine; mix with milk mixture.
Add fruit and nuts to mixture.
Press into a waxed paper lined pan and let stand overnight.
Keep refrigerated and the longer you keep, the better it is.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate over hot water (not boiling). Let cool.
In bowl, mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add shortening and sour cream; beat 2 minutes.
Add egg, vanilla, melted chocolate and hot water.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour in 2 (8-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: pork steak special
directions: Bring a large pan of water to boil and remove from heat. Place cabbage leaves in water for 5 minutes to soften.
Cook rice. Brown steaks and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Season tomatoes with salt and pepper.
May add cayenne pepper if desired. Place a couple of leaves of cabbage for each steak.
Place steaks on leaves.
Spoon rice on steak.
Ladle tomatoes with juice over rice.
Cover with a couple of leaves per steak.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: picadillo dip
directions: Brown beef; drain any grease.
Add remaining ingredients. simmer 2 hours, stirring frequently.
Serve in chafing dish with tortilla chips.

title: lemon custard cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool, then poke cake full of holes with a fork.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together good.
Cook low and slow.
Stir all the time. Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites on high speed with 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Pour on pie.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix jello in 1 cup of hot water and the Kool-aid according to instructions.
Add mashed or cut-up bananas and other ingredients. This may be frozen, if so, take out of freezer and place in refrigerator for approximately 5 hours to thaw to a mushy consistency.
Just before serving, add 1 quart of ginger ale, if desired.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, almonds, celery, onion, chicken broth, mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice, pepper and seasoned salt.
Pour in pan.
Top with crackers.
Sprinkle with 1 stick melted margarine. Bake at 350° until bubbly and light brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix; beat until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Gradually add flour and baking soda (after mixing together).
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pudding delite
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and pat into a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Whip together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust.
Top with pudding made with only 3 cups milk.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: tuna chop suey
directions: Saute onion and garlic powder in salad oil.
Melt cornstarch in water and add onion mixture with seasoning and soy sauce.
Heat until thick and clear.
Stir in rice and tuna.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir and serve with chow mein noodles or extra rice.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
boiling water.
Immediately add ice cream and
stir
until
mixture is smooth and free from lumps. Place in
refrigerator
for 15 minutes.
Remove and add thawed strawberries.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Return to refrigerator for at least three hours.
Decorate with whipped cream (optional).

title: squaw corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: green tomato cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add eggs, oil and sugar to the mixture.
Beat well.
Pour batter into greased deep-dish pan or two large Bundt pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread on cookie sheet and cook until crisp.
Rub bread with the garlic clove.
Cut bread into 2-inch squares.

title: millionaires or pralines
directions: Combine sugars, syrup, margarine and 1 cup of milk.
Stir well and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add other cup of milk gradually while stirring.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into large buttered pan.
Cool at room temperature and slice.

title: croquettes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour; gradually add milk to make a thick sauce.
Add parsley, onion, chicken and lemon juice.
Add seasonings; shape into cylinders.
Blend lightly beaten egg and water.
Roll cylinders in bread crumbs, then in egg mixture, then into crumbs again.
Chill.
Heat oil to 385° and fry croquettes until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° 1 hour on lower rack.

title: old fashioned new york chili in 20 minutes
directions: Brown meat and peppers and onion in large pan with oil.
Add tomato sauce and salsa.
Cook stirring often.
Add beans and heat 5 more minutes.
Serve with hard rolls or corn bread.

title: fat free salad dressing
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients through blender for half a minute on high speed.
Pour into saucepan; stir constantly on high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil hard for 1/2 minute.
Remove from heat.
Whisk in the last 3 ingredients.
Cool.
Will keep for 3 weeks.

title: energy cookies
directions: Add these ingredients and mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.

title: shrimp and okra gumbo
directions: Remove heads
of
shrimp;
wash
thoroughly;
then boil about 10	minutes.
Chop	okra
fine; mince onions.
Fry okra, onion and pepper
slightly.	Add
chopped up tomatoes.
Fry a few minutes then add two quarts of boiling water, in which the shrimp have been cooked.
Boil	for
about
hours on a slow fire.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix together and beat dry ingredients, soup and shortening for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and water; beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour an 11 x 18-inch pan.
In a bowl, stir together first five ingredients; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat at medium speed the next four ingredients until well blended. Gradually add flour mixture.
With spoon stir in carrots and walnuts.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat together on high speed the solid shortening, butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar until thoroughly combined, about 5 minutes. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the vanilla and lemon juice.
In a bowl, stir together the soda, salt, cinnamon, oats and flour. Beat dry ingredients into the creamed mixture until well combined.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl.
Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal until all pieces are covered.
Pour cereal into large plastic bag with powdered sugar. Shake until all pieces are covered.
Pour into bowl and let cool. Ready to eat.

title: potato souffle
directions: Boil potatoes with salt and pepper.
Broil onion.
Drain potatoes and onion.
Add butter, cream cheese, egg, chives and bacon bits.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mother's homemade noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Roll thick or thin as you like. Cut in strips; let set for about 2 hours to dry. Drop in boiling chicken or beef broth. Cook about 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in oil, just enough to soften. Dip in enchilada sauce and put 1 layer in oblong pan.
Add 1 layer of chicken, 1 layer of soups (blended together) and 1 layer of cheeses. Continue layers until all ingredients are used.
Reserve some shredded cheese for top.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together egg, buttermilk or sour milk, onion and water; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add egg mixture to cornmeal mixture; stir just until moistened.
Drop batter by tablespoons into deep hot fat (375°).
Fry about 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper toweling or bags.
Makes about 24.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Mix well and pour into prepared ring mold.
Chill. Serve with topping.

title: chocolate caramel layer squares
directions: Stir in 1 cup quick cooking rolled oats, 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Strain and put broth into deep pan.
To make noodles, use 1 egg and flour to make drops that you can handle.
Drop the egg mixture into the boiling broth.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix the chicken, celery, grapes and onion.
Separately mix the mayonnaise or yogurt with the curry powder and pepper.
Stir the dressing into the chicken mixture and serve.

title: gala pecan spread
directions: Mix softened cheese with milk.
Stir in beef, green pepper, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon into glass dish with cover.
Crisp pecans in margarine and salt on medium heat for 1 minute.
Sprinkle pecans on top of spread.
Heat for 5 minutes on medium high.
Serve with party rye.

title: blender cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumber into blender container.
Cover; blend on high speed until pureed.
Stop blender to push cucumber down from side of container.
Add water to puree if necessary to make 1 cup. Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/4 cups of boiling water.
Add cucumber. Chill until partially thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Pour into 3-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Serves 4.
As desired vegetable exchange.
Serve with cottage cheese dressing.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Slowly blend in cream cheese with corn.
Add diced chillies. Bring ingredients to boil.
Simmer until cheese is thoroughly melted.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: honeyed apple drink
directions: In large micro-safe mug combine all ingredients.
Cook on High for 1 to 2 minutes until warm, stirring halfway through and at the end of cooking.
Makes 1 serving.

title: creamy dill dressing or dip
directions: Mix together.
Can be made 3 days in advance and refrigerated. Good for dipping veggies or as salad dressing.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl. This dough will keep in the refrigerator up to 5 or 6 weeks in a tightly covered bowl. Bake them as you need them. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 50 muffins.

title: venison skillet supper
directions: In large skillet, combine onion, green pepper and ground venison.
Cook over medium heat until meat is brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Stir.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in beans until well heated.
Top with corn chips and serve.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, water, sugar and ginger.
Marinate chicken in sauce for 1 hour.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice and sauce.

title: fat-free oven baked french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into strips.
Arrange on Teflon baking sheet after dipping each strip into liquid Butter Buds or brushing Butter Buds on potatoes.
Optional seasoning to use is garlic, onion or chili powder instead of salt.
Sprinkle to taste.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn; bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: ponsit
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cool and dice.
Save 2 cups broth.
Add oil to wok and cook on low heat.
Add garlic, onion, celery, cabbage, green pepper and carrots and stir-fry on high until tender.
Add 1 cup broth and steam for a few minutes.
When you start to stir-fry, add water to the rice sticks and let stand until frying is done.
Drain and add to veggies.
Add chicken and soy sauce.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and bell pepper in large bowl.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Cut the apples and oranges into small pieces, leaving the peeling on.
Cook all together 2 to 3 minutes, after bringing to a hard boil.
Add 1 pound cranberries, rinsed; stir constantly, mashing on side of pan.
When cranberries are all popped it's ready.
Cool and refrigerate.
Stays good for 2 weeks.

title: ham and shell salad
directions: Cook large shells according to package directions and drain. Rinse with cool water and drain.
In a large bowl combine shells and remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Chill; it makes 6 servings.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Saute pork chops in hot oil in an electric skillet set at 300° for 15 minutes, turning once; drain.
Top pork chops with vegetables; dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to 220°, cover and cook 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove meat and vegetables to serving platter, reserving drippings in skillet.
Combine flour and 1 cup water, mixing until smooth.
Add salt to gravy while it's cooking.
Gradually add mixture to drippings.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Serve sauce with meat and vegetables.

title: apple-carrot quick bread
directions: In a bowl blend apples and carrots.
Add butter, lemon extract and eggs.
Beat to mix.
Sift together flour, sugar, powder, soda and salt.
Add to apple and carrot mixture.
Stir in nuts if desired.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done when tested with toothpick. Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing.
Put bread on a rack to complete cooling.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Mix flour and margarine.
Cook to make sauce.
Dice cheese and let melt in sauce.
In a buttered baking dish, place a layer of cracker crumbs and moisten with sauce.
Add chopped eggs and pimentos.
Repeat with sauce then top with the remaining cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or microwave for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheeseburger skillet dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, brown the turkey or beef with the onion.
Drain.
Stir in vegetables, ketchup, water, mustard and garlic powder.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add Cheddar cheese and stir until melted.
Mix in macaroni and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix and cook until it forms a ball when tested in a cup of cold water (about 10 minutes from a full boil).
Remove from heat.
Add teaspoon vanilla then add 2 cups chopped pecans or your choice. Pour into 2 buttered platters or pan.
Cool and cut.

title: last minute cake
directions: Empty can of peaches into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam and spread them evenly over the bottom.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches (do not stir).
Melt butter and pour over dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream sugar and margarine with a wooden spoon.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In small bowl, stir together flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Stir into butter mixture until well mixed.
In same small bowl combine 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Turn oven to 375°.

title: dip for chips
directions: Drain and chop tomatoes.
Add taco relish.
Melt cheese; stir in.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk and oil; add to dry ingredients.
Stir just to moisten.
Drop by tablespoons directly onto chicken in boiling broth.
Cover tightly and return to boiling.
Reduce heat (do not lift lid).
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
I boil 12 minutes.
Makes 10 dumplings.

title: 24-hour vegetable salad
directions: Mix and marinate.
It can be eaten in 1 1/2 hours, but best if chilled overnight.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and soda and add to butter mixture, alternating with sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or 10-inch Bundt pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in preheated 325° oven or until cake tests done.
Cool for 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat cooking oil to 375° in deep fryer.
Mix together in a bowl the first 6 ingredients.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add a mixture of the milk and egg all at once.
Mix until well blended.
Using about 1 heaping tablespoon for each, form into small cakes.
Deep-fry only as many cakes at one time as will float uncrowded one layer deep in the hot fat.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes or until well browned.
Turn cakes with tongs as they rise to the surface several times during cooking.
Lift and drain over fat before draining on absorbent paper.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: toffee bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Spread dough on a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or lightly brown.
Spread immediately with chocolate bits; let stand a few minutes.
Spread chocolate evenly over top; sprinkle with pecans.
Cool.
Cut into bars, about 3 1/2 dozen.
Cut with pizza cutter.

title: willie's tarragon chicken
directions: Sprinkle fryer with spices.
Spread over with sour cream. Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: grandma's strawberry preserves
directions: Put two cups sugar over berries and cook slowly on low heat. Shake pan until sugar has dissolved.
Add the other two cups of sugar and cook until sugar has melted.
Turn up heat and cook rapidly for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, mushrooms, eggs and 2 tablespoons onion; stir in mayonnaise, sour cream and salt.
Place pineapple slices on lettuce-lined plates.
Top each with chicken salad. Garnish with remaining onion and cherry tomatoes.

title: frosted lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello, water and fruit.
Set until firm.
Cook pineapple juice, beaten egg, flour and Dream Whip until thick.
Put on top of salad.

title: apple crisp
directions: *Or 1 quart canned apple pie filling.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil and eggs and beat.
Add carrots and blend.
Pour into oiled and floured cake pans (3 round).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix and spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: little cherry cheesecakes
directions: Beat
cream
cheese
until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla
and
lemon
juice.
Place	wafer in bottom of cupcake paper.
Fill
paper 3/4 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20	minutes or until filling is puffed.
Place a maraschino cherry or a spoonful of cherry pie filling on after baked.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and yellow food coloring (if desired).
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 30 minutes; cool. Spread with whipped cream.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Place in large bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: boiled fudge cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. (Start timing after mixture reaches full rolling boil.) Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts or coconut.
Beat until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix broccoli, soup, sour cream, water chestnuts, onion and cheese together. Pour into casserole dish. Top with crackers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cook sugar, flour, butter, eggs and juice until thick.
Cool. Add pineapple, nuts, marshmallows and whipped cream.
Serve over angel food cake.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in large roaster for five hours at 250°.

title: baked onions a la potato chips
directions: Use a greased casserole dish and place in layers the sliced onions, crushed potato chips and grated cheese.
Blend mushroom soup and milk and pour over the top of all layers.
Sprinkle dry mustard over top of this and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin.
Add flour, salt, nutmeg, allspice, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix alternately with water.
Add chopped pecans and raisins.
Bake in 2 loaf pans or a tube pan sprayed with Pam for 1 hour at 350°. Remove from oven.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Set on cooling rack.
Slice and serve.

title: special dessert
directions: Mix and place in oblong pan.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix powdered sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add pineapple and apple chunks.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Just before serving, add peanuts.
If put in too soon, they'll get soggy.

title: fluffy white filling
directions: Place flour in a small saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add salt, vanilla and flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Yield: about 4 cups.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Remove all visible fat from tamales.
In shallow baking dish, place tamales in single layer.
Cover with chili.
Sprinkle chopped onion over top.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes. Sprinkle grated cheese over casserole and bake just long enough to melt the cheese.
Serve hot.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Brown bacon slightly.
Add onion and fry until bacon is crisp. Add catsup and brown sugar and blend well, including all bacon fat. Simmer 2 minutes.
Pour over green beans in an oblong cake pan or casserole.
Do not stir.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, flour, sugar and salt; stir well. Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well; stir into corn mixture.
Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring twice during first 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Bake in a shallow cookie sheet.
After cake is cooled, use a large cookie or biscuit cutter and cut into small round cakes.

title: clam dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender or food processor.
Blend to desired consistency.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, onions and peppers.
Add cheese and milk. Mix salt and meal.
Add corn and mix well.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: krazy kake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into
an 8-inch square baking pan. Make a well in the center,
put
in
the moist ingredients and mix well. Bake at 325°
until
done.
This
cake is delicious with a broiled coconut frosting.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Use juice to dissolve sugar.
Add Jell-O to hot water; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until set.

title: almond chicken nuggets with honey mustard dipping sauce
directions: In a shallow dish mix together vegetable oil, lemon juice and soy sauce.
Add chicken.
Toss to coat.
Marinate 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Combine the egg whites, sugar, salt, lemon juice and thawed strawberries in a large bowl.
Beat on high for 10 minutes.
Pour into a serving bowl and freeze (covered with Saran Wrap).

title: applesauce and peanut butter cake
directions: Mix well all of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Good moist cake.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese and onion rings).
Put in greased casserole dish; cover top with cheese after baking for 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle onion over top; bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour into molds and refrigerate.

title: snack bars
directions: Grease pan.
Melt butter and marshmallows.
Stir constantly. Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Stir in milk and breakfast drink.
Fold in raisins and cereal, stirring until evenly coated. With buttered hands, pat evenly into pan.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: apricot chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Gradually add sugar and beat well after each addition.
Add apricot puree, orange rind and lemon juice.
Cook on simmer, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and beat until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in fruit mixture.
Pour into baked shell and chill thoroughly.
The filling must be very cold to cut well.

title: cheezy salsa dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Add cheese and salsa. Simmer for 10 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Mix 2 heaping teaspoonfuls with hot water and sweeten if needed.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a large heavy skillet, heat butter and oil until hot but not smoking.
Add garlic and shallots and saute until golden brown.
Add all vegetables and basil and cook quickly so that they are heated through but crisp.
It should take about 5 minutes. Spoon the sauce over cooked and drained pasta of your choice.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Save 2 tablespoons for topping.
Press into spring-form pan.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, egg yolks and food coloring.
Pour into pan and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Add sugar and vanilla to sour cream and pour over filling.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes at 475°.
Cool and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: oyster pie
directions: Parboil potatoes, celery
and carrot until fork-tender. Drain. Layer vegetables and oysters
in
baking pan.
Dot top with butter; pour heated milk over.
Add
top
crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: creamy vegetables in pastry shells
directions: Prepare pastry shells according to package directions. Meanwhile, in 1-quart saucepan combine soup and milk.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring often.
Evenly divide hot cooked vegetables among pastry shells.
Spoon sauce over vegetables and pastry shells.
Serves 6.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients, 1/4 teaspoon of salt and pepper in a 10-inch ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat 5 to 7 minutes, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink. Remove mixture from skillet, drain. Wipe skillet clean with paper towels.

title: stuffed green pepper
directions: Cut peppers in half and remove seeds.
In skillet, heat oil. Add onion and garlic.
Add meat and stir until brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tomato sauce and beef consomme.
Cool a little and stuff peppers.
Place peppers in greased baking dish and pour tomato sauce around.
Pour one can beef consomme on and around peppers.
Use other can to pour while cooking to prevent drying.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: southern-style barbecue chicken
directions: Combine soup, honey, mustard and onion powder.
Arrange chicken, bone side up, on rack in broiler pan.
Brush chicken with sauce.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear, turning once and brushing often with sauce during cooking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend 10 seconds at a time, 3 or 4 times.
Pour into buttered and floured 10-inch pie dish and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pie will be done with top is golden brown.

title: salsa marinated chuck steak
directions: *Hoisin sauce is available in the imported (Oriental) section of the grocery store.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix and form ball.
Roll in about 3/4 cup chopped pecans.

title: turnip souffle
directions: Peel and cook turnips until tender; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350°.

title: milky way cake
directions: Snickers bars are good too.

title: mounds candy bar
directions: Mix together coconut, confectioners sugar, margarine, vanilla and milk; press into 2 long Pyrex dishes and chill overnight or place in freezer 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler over low heat.
Stir to blend.
Cut coconut into squares and using toothpicks, dip into chocolate mixture.
Let cool on waxed paper or foil.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sweet and sour rice
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a simmer, then add onion and green pepper.
Cook another minute.
Pour over rice.
Stir and serve.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix pineapple and marshmallows.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix pineapple juice, flour, sugar, vinegar and beaten egg over low to medium heat until thick.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, mix Cool Whip with refrigerated items, add apples and nuts.
Leave some nuts to sprinkle over top.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening well. Add vanilla. Gradually add powdered sugar, then add milk. Mix well. Can be stored in covered container in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crackers with melted stick of oleo.
Press in 8 or 9-inch pie tin.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons oleo until clear, not brown.
Spoon into crust.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper. Pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Sprinkle with parsley.
This goes well with a dinner or as an appetizer.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together.
Add all other ingredients which
have
been
mixed together.
Mix well; pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: bumsteads
directions: Stuff rolls and wrap in foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts.
May be frozen, then reheated.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown first 2 ingredients and drain off grease.
Add next 2 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in Velveeta cheese.
Mix well. When cheese is melted, spread on party rye bread slices.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple with juice to a boil, add Jello, stir until dissolved, let cool some.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip, mix well, add nuts and chill before serving.

title: pineapple christmas salad
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups
liquid.
Heat to boiling and pour over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved. Stir in pineapple and remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and chop.
Mix with other ingredients. Use bread crumbs or dry package of dressing with melted margarine to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey butter
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy; gradually add honey, beating well. Beat in lemon rind. Chill butter mixture several hours or overnight. Serve Honey Butter with muffins or toast. Yields 1 cup.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in a heavy kettle. Add Soup. Cover and cook over low heat until meat is done. (3-4 Hours) Remove meat, thicken gravy as desired using a smooth paste made by blending water with flour.

title: friendship tea(spiced orange tea)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Store in a tightly covered container. For each serving, stir 2 rounded teaspoonfuls into 6 ounces water (cold or boiling).
Is wonderful hot or cold.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef and set aside. Mix all ingredients, except dried beef, together. Mix well with hands like you would knead dough. Add a small portion of dried beef and continue to mix thoroughly. When finished mixing, shape into a large ball, using all of the cream cheese mixture. Roll ball into remaining dried beef to coat. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Pour pudding mix over and stir.
Add marshmallows and stir.
Refrigerate.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and vinegar to 240°.
Pour slowly on egg whites, beating until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla and drop in lumps on waxed paper or spread in buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into steak. Melt fat in skillet and sear steak on both sides. Remove steak to large casserole or roaster.

There should be at least 2 tablespoons fat remaining in the skillet. To this add the flour and blend; stir in tomatoes, seasonings and onion. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Pour over steak; cover roaster and bake in 350° oven until tender, about 3 hours.

title: puppy chow
directions: Combine chocolate chips and butter.
Heat and stir until melted.
Place cereal in a large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Stir in peanut butter. Place powdered sugar in a large plastic bag.
Add coated cereal mixture.
Close bag and shake until well coated.
Makes about 16 cups.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch glass baking pan melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: spinach salad with sesame dressing
directions: Toss together in salad bowl.
Pour Sesame Dressing over and toss gently.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ground turkey barley soup
directions: Brown turkey in large saucepan, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle flour over meat and stir until flour loses its white color.
Slowly add broth, then remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 60 minutes.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil for 1 minute, turning occasionally. Drain.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, mushrooms, zucchini and basil. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Serve over pasta.

title: becnel peas and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add small amount of flour for light roux.
Add tomatoes (chopped) and cook down.
Add peas with liquid of one can only.
Cook down.
Add sliced boiled egg before serving.

title: american chop suey
directions: Saute diced vegetables in oil until tender; add meat and brown.
Cook macaroni.
Stir flour into stewed tomatoes.
Add all ingredients together.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: orange cake snack
directions: Cut
top from an orange.
Eat pulp.
Pour prepared cake batter into shell.
Replace top.
Wrap in foil and bake.

title: heath dessert
directions: Follow directions
on
box
for pudding, using 1/2 milk called for.
Mix pudding with ice cream and spread over graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate
until set.
Spread Cool Whip over the top. Crush
Heath
bars	into
bits and sprinkle over the top.
Chill.

title: incredible edibles
directions: Blend together graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Melt together, in a double boiler, butter or margarine and peanut butter.

title: fried cheese
directions: Cut
cheese
into 1-inch cubes;
toss in flour.
Dip in egg; roll in crumbs seasoned with oregano and basil.
Refrigerate
at least
30 minutes.
Heat 1-inch peanut oil in heavy skillet
Fry quickly (about 30 seconds). Serve with tomato sauce. Takes about 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar all at once.
Blend with a spoon just until flour is all moistened.
This is an easy crust to handle and can be re-rolled without toughening.
Keep in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Can be frozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes and butter.
Melt butter; pour over ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
After 30 minutes, put corn flakes on top and continue baking.

title: doris' pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add vanilla, egg and buttermilk; mix well.
Makes 1 quart.

title: squaw corn
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add undiluted soup, melted margarine and corn.
Cover with grated cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion in skillet; drain. Add Ragu sauce, tomato sauce, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; simmer on low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add sliced cheese; allow to melt just before pouring up.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry onion in butter until tender.
Add rice, soy sauce, pepper, parsley and garlic salt.
Cook over low heat 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add egg, stirring constantly. Cook on low heat 5 minutes more.

title: zucchini stir-fry
directions: Cut all your vegetables into small pieces.
Put small amount of oil in skillet.
Add vegetables when oil is hot.
Stir.
Add desired amount of soy sauce.
Start by adding few drops of fruit, gradually adding more.
Cook until done.
Some prefer vegetables crunchy, others prefer theirs soft.
Serve over cooked rice.
This dish is also good with chicken or steak cooked and cut into small pieces and added to vegetables.

title: chocolate butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except flour and cocoa.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy, 2 to 3 minutes.
Gradually add flour and cocoa until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls as desired (balls, logs, flattened, etc.).
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes, or until set.
Cool. Decorate (if desired) with melted chocolate chips, nuts, maraschino cherries, etc.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion, garlic, green pepper, ground beef and stew meat in hog fat or bacon drippings.
Add chili powder, salt, paprika, cayenne pepper, cloves, bay leaf, cumin seed and tomatoes.
Simmer for 2 hours, adding water if necessary.
Add beans; heat through. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fat-free dilled potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard, dill, salt and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan and heat thoroughly.

title: orange papaya smoothie
directions: Puree or process all ingredients until smooth.
Serve in tall glasses.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Break up into pieces and set aside.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat and push crescent rolls into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat softened cream cheese and milk. Spread over crust and cool.
Top with your selection of vegetables and shredded cheese.

title: surprise oyster nibbles
directions: Combine vegetable oil, dressing mix and dill weed; stir well. Place oyster crackers in a large bowl.
Add oil mixture; toss gently to coat.
Place in an airtight container, cover and let stand 24 hours before serving.
Store at room temperature for up to 3 weeks.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: fruit bake
directions: The night before, drain all fruit.
Pour into 2-quart square pan.
In saucepan, melt butter. Stir in sugar, cornstarch and sherry. Cook on low until thick and smooth.
Pour over fruit and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately. Serves 10.

title: taco stir-fry
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in oil in a large skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Stir in corn, tomatoes and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup of cheese and corn chips. Cook until cheese is partially melted.
Place lettuce on serving platter.
Spoon ground beef mixture over top.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Yields 6 servings, about 580 calories each.

title: cabbage dish and chapati
directions: Saute cabbage in oil.
Add a pinch of salt.
Remove from the stove.
Then saute the chopped onion, tomatoes, chicken seasoning, milk and mushroom soup.
Pour into the sauteed cabbage.
Let stand on stove for 10 minutes and stir.
Serve with rice and chapaties.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt together in microwave.
Salt to taste.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons flour mixed with 1/3 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix;
pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: mini sausage quiches
directions: Beat the butter or margarine and cream cheese in a medium bowl until creamy.
Blend in flour; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll into 24 (1 inch) balls and press each into mini muffin cups.

title: ham and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Add all other ingredients, mix well, and chill for a least 6 hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jean's clusters
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Boil until mixture is clear and free from sugar crystals.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add cereal and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Clusters will harden as they cool.
Makes about 20 clusters.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli and chicken in baking dish.
Blend soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle grated cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: "chicken that makes its own gravy"
directions: Melt margarine in pan while hot. Place chicken in pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes on each side.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook squash covered in boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain and mash enough squash to measure 1 cup. Reserve any remaining squash for use in other recipes.
Combine the 1 cup of mashed squash and egg.
Stir well.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Add squash mixture and onion.
Stir until blended.
Drop squash mixture by level tablespoonful into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain well on paper towels.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to
Soften
butter
or margarine to room temperature.
Blend mix, water, eggs and butter.
Beat at medium speed for 4
minutes.
Grease
sides and bottom of each pan. Flour lightly.
Pour enough batter for 5 or 6 layers.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Split dates and stuff each half with pecan section.
Spoon a dab of cream cheese on top of pecan section and roll each stuffed date in powdered sugar.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix together and cook slow until desired thickness, about 1 hour.
Seal in pint jars.
Makes 9 or 10 pints.

title: ground beef 'n' biscuits
