directions: Cook meat, celery and onion together; drain. Stir in flour, salt, oregano and pepper until blended. Add tomato sauce and peas; simmer for 5 minutes. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Separate biscuits; arrange over beef mixture. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden and cheese is melted. Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Cook all ingredients in saucepan for 15 to 20 minutes or until preserves sheet off spoon like jelly.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: butternut squash souffle
directions: Mix the ingredients in the order listed and turn into a well buttered baking dish.
Lightly cover the top with coconut and bake at 350° until coconut is golden yellow or souffle is hot.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix ingredients and put on top of the other mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: yogurt deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and set whites aside.
Mash yolks with fork.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Refill whites using about 1 tablespoon yolk mixture for each egg half.

title: crab stuffed shrimp
directions: Peel, devein and butterfly shrimp, leaving tails on.
Cook shrimp in boiling water for 1 minute.
Remove; set aside. Saute onion, celery and green pepper in margarine until tender. Set aside.
Mix crab meat and the next 6 ingredients.
Add sauteed onion, celery and green pepper.
Top each shrimp with 3 tablespoons crab mixture.
Wrap bacon around entire shrimp. Drizzle 1/4 cup margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then broil 6 minutes.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Combine sugars, milk, butter and salt.
Cook gently, stirring frequently, until it comes to gentle boil.
Cook on medium heat to 235° on candy thermometer or soft ball stage, stirring.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat with long handled wooden spoon.
Add pecans.
Beat only until it begins to thicken.
Quickly drop onto foil.
Wrap in wax paper when cool or store in container.

title: upside down pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add and cook celery, onion and green pepper. Add salt and tomato soup.
Combine Bisquick and water.
Roll and pat dough into a circle slightly smaller than skillet.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups, broth, tarragon and vegetables.
Pour over chicken.

title: pennsylvania dutch salad dressing(potato salad, macaroni, lettuce, spinach)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, water and vinegar.
Make a paste from flour and water.
Add to ingredients.
Cook until thick. Pour over cooked, diced potatoes, 7 or 8.
Better made the day before.

title: 1015 casserole
directions: Melt
cup	butter	and
saute onions until tender. Place 1/2
onions
in a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs over onions.
Repeat layers of onions and remaining cup of cheese.

title: punch
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in Ziploc bags and freeze (Kool-Aid mixture) or in 1/2 gallon milk jugs.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Add last 2 ingredients. Stir gently; serve.

title: orange cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach.
In a large bowl, toss spinach, oranges, cauliflower, green pepper and dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Cook roast in oven or crock-pot until meat is done and pulls apart easily.
Shred meat (or slice if you prefer).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour onto shredded meat and mix well.
Let mixture cook in warm oven or crock-pot for at least an hour, stirring occasionally.

title: old fashion yeast rolls
directions: Let butter and Crisco dissolve in warm milk.
Combine yeast with 1/2 cup warm water and dissolve.
Stir in half of flour and remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Use hands to mix in enough remaining flour until dough cleans bowl.
Place onto lightly floured surface.
Cover and let stand for approximately 20 minutes. Knead until smooth.
Cover with cloth and let rise in warm place for approximately 1 hour or until double in size.
Knead again with lightly buttered hands and let rise again for approximately 1/2 hour.
Divide into 2 parts (if loaves are desired) or pinch off small portions to shape rolls.
Let rise approximately 20 minutes. Place in warm oven (200°).
Increase heat to 425°.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: mom's peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly. Stir in peanut butter. Sift dry ingredients together, then stir into creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheets. Press with the back of a fork to make crisscross. Bake in oven at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Makes about 10 dozen cookies.

title: shish kabob chicken
directions: Mix together vegetable oil, corn syrup, soy sauce, vinegar, garlic and ginger.
Pour over chicken and marinate 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Drain well, saving marinade.
Arrange chicken, vegetables and fruit alternately on long skewers.
Grill over hot coals about 4 inches from heat 10 to 12 minutes.
Baste and turn occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, oleo and nuts.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar; spread over first mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes (until golden brown).
Do not overbake.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Boil sugar and Karo syrup for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter. Add mixture to Rice Krispies and mix well.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and top with chocolate chips and butterscotch chips (melted together).
Cut the mixture while warm.

title: fudge nuggets
directions: Melt chocolate squares in double boiler or in microwave.
In 2-quart pot, pour melted chocolate, margarine, sugar and cream. Cook to soft ball stage on medium heat (or for 5 minutes). Remove from heat and add graham cracker crumbs, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until almost set.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cool and cut into squares.
Place on candy dish.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook, cool, debone and shred chicken.
Cook, cool and chop broccoli.
Spread broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and pat down gently.
Top with shredded chicken.
Mix together next 6 ingredients.
Spread over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat, onion and green chiles.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 60 minutes.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon and set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer beat butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream.
Beat until combined.
Turn 1/3 of batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 blueberries and 1/2 cinnamon-brown sugar mixture.
Repeat layering and bake 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Gently remove.
Drizzle with icing (1 cup confectioners sugar and 1 to 2 tablespoons milk).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, spices and sugar.
Add all other ingredients; mix until smooth.
Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade ranch dressing
directions: Whisk all ingredients together until smooth and well combined. Refrigerate overnight to let flavors blend.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix in blender; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake until solid (probably another 20 minutes).

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar; let come to a boil.
Mix jello with 1/2 cup hot water and let dissolve.
Add jello to pineapple mixture and set in refrigerator until almost jelled.
Fold in cream cheese, whipped cream and nuts.
Chill until set.
Unmold.

title: cream of mushroom soup(1 cup)
directions: Wash and chop mushrooms.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons water and 1 tablespoon of oil.
Whiz tofu 2 to 3 minutes in blender until very smooth with 1 cup of water and cornstarch. Stir a little and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: summer dream salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and boiling water.
Mix well.
Add defrosted lemonade.
Mix and refrigerate until jelly like.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour into mold.
When ready to serve, unmold and fill center with fresh fruit:
grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Heat soup, milk and butter. Layer potatoes, onions, soup mixture and bacon. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza chicken wings
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Dip drummettes in butter.
Then coat in dry mixture.
Place on foil-lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mash sweet potatoes; add all other ingredients.
Spread in buttered baking dish.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Fill tortillas with pie filling.
Roll up and layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt butter or oleo with sugar and water. Pour over tortillas and bake 40 minutes in a 325° oven.
Sprinkle with cinnamon before baking.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Heat milk and egg yolks; add mixed sugar and flour.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut, vanilla and butter.
Mix and pour into prebaked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and add.
Then brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut it up and put it in a bowl and put whipped topping over it.

title: frozen butterfinger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place graham crackers in a food processor; pulse until crumbly. Add butter and egg white; pulse until moist. Press crumb mixture into a 9-inch pie plate coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes; cool on a wire rack 15 minutes Freeze 15 minutes.

title: pickled squash
directions: Soak squash and onion in ice and salt for 1 hour.
In pot, put vinegar, sugar, mustard and celery seed; bring to boil.
In clean pint jars put the squash and onion after it has been rinsed and drained.
Pour the boiling vinegar mixture over squash.
Seal jars immediately.

title: lizzie's mixed vegetable salad
directions: Drain macaroni, vegetables and beans.
Combine with dressing.

title: deluxe strawberry preserves(i love these preserves on homemade bread or toast.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix strawberries and sugar.
Stir and let stand 10 minutes.
In saucepan, boil Sure-Jell in water for 1 minute.
Stir in strawberries and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and put into containers or sterile glass jars.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours before eating.

title: cherry angel food trifle
directions: Mix well the sugar and cream cheese.
Reserve enough Cool Whip for top decoration.
Mix the rest into sugar and cream cheese mixture; add pecans.
Layer cake cubes, sugar mixture and pie filling in pretty bowl, ending with pie filling on top.
Dot with remaining Cool Whip for decoration.

title: apple-filled bran muffins
directions: For apple filling, in a small mixing bowl, stir together apple, nuts, brown sugar, margarine or butter and cinnamon; set aside.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Slice 1/4 of potatoes, carrots and celery.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Put 1/2 of ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover mixture with hamburger; put rest of veggies in.
Spread tomato soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: strawberry pastries
directions: Roll each sheet of pastry dough out to about 12 x 6-inch.
Cut into 4 even pieces.
Cover baking sheet with waxed paper.
Place dough on sheet.
Prick with fork.
Sift powdered sugar over dough. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes. Increase temperature to 450°.
Bake another 3 to 5 minutes until light golden and puffed.

title: pork chops with tomatoes
directions: Salt and pepper chops to taste.
Combine chops, onion and bell pepper in a large skillet.
Cook until vegetables are tender and chops are lightly browned.
Pour off excess grease and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for approximately 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: creamed cheese and potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Drain and mash with all ingredients, except chives, paprika and butter.
Beat until light and fluffy. Stir in chives and put into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: peanut butter icebox pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar until creamy. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese with 1 stick margarine in double boiler.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons oleo in skillet.
Add shrimp and saute until shrimp is pink.
Drain water from shrimp mixture.
Add shrimp mixture to cream cheese and oleo in large mixing bowl; add soup, seasonings and rice.
Mix well; pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mrs. fritz's nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in loaf pan (greased and floured). Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: devil's food cake(made with salad dressing)
directions: Mix salad dressing and sugar.
Put soda in cocoa and add to hot water.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° to 350° for about 40 minutes (325° for glass pan).
Use an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: roasted dill chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix together the Italian dressing, dill, onions, salt and pepper until blended. Place chicken in roasting pan, spread dill mixture inside cavity and over skin.
Coat potatoes with remaining dill mixture.
Place potatoes around chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil and roast for 1 1/2 hours, turning potatoes occasionally.
Remove foil and continue to cook until chicken and potatoes are completely done.

title: apple bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Combine the flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Mix, then add the chopped and peeled apples and nuts.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with sugar when you remove from pans.
Wrap while hot to freeze.

title: georgia soup
directions: *I use cabbage instead of butter beans.

title: mint mist pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in medium bowl till light and fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk, mint extract and food coloring. Beat mixture till smooth.
Gently fold in Cool Whip with rubber spatula.
Fold in chocolate pieces.
Spoon into pie crust.
Place in freezer till hardened, at least 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with chocolate pieces and mint leaves, if you wish.
Serves 6.

title: crab imperial ii
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: easy pepper pasta
directions: Thinly slice the halves of peppers.
Saute in 2 tablespoons of olive oil and garlic, if you choose, until tender-crisp.
Toss with basil, cooked pasta and red pepper flakes for that extra oomph!

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and stir until smooth.
Batter should be medium thin.
Grease muffin tins or iron skillet and bake until brown on top.

title: kentucky ginger-molasses cake
directions: Mix together the eggs, sugar, molasses, oil and spices in large bowl; beat well.
Dissolve soda in 2 teaspoons warm water; add to mixture.
Add flour and boiling water.
Beat well; mixture will be very thin.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook for approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk for 1 minute.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla; beat well. May add mini marshmallows, if desired.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients until well blended. Add pecans. Pour into pie crust. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in 1/2 cup canned milk.
Mix ground beef, onion, egg, nutmeg, salt and pepper into crumbs.
Shape into walnut size balls; fry in butter until browned on all sides.
Take them out of the pan and stir flour into juice that remains.
Add the other 1/2 cup of milk and cup of hot water.
Heat this mixture until sauce thickens.
Put meat balls and sauce into covered baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: spinach rice
directions: Cook spinach and green beans with butter, parsley, garlic powder, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Cook wild rice according to box directions.
Combine everything into one dish.

title: water chestnut balls
directions: Cut bacon in half and wrap around chestnuts; stick with toothpicks.
Broil for 7 minutes (turn).
Put in baking dish.
Mix up sugar and catsup and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: german pancakes
directions: Beat eggs lightly with electric mixer.
Beat in flour, salt, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat until batter is smooth and light. Let batter rest about 5 minutes.
Melt butter in heavy 12-inch skillet.
When hot, pour in 1/2 cup batter, tilting skillet to spread batter over entire bottom of skillet.
Cook until small bubbles form.
Turn; brown.
Slip onto plate; spread with butter and syrup and roll jelly roll fashion.
Makes 6 large pancakes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form mixture into 4 long rolls and wrap with waxed paper.
Chill or freeze.
Slice and put on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: peppy turkey casserole
directions: Melt butter in glass baking dish; set aside. Place turkey in casserole dish. Set cheese on top of turkey. Layer pepperoni over cheese. Top with stuffing. Microwave on High for 6 minutes, turning at 3 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: kerrville banana crunch punch
directions: Boil water and sugar 3 minutes and cool.
Add rest of ingredients to cooled syrup and freeze.
When ready to serve, mix with 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine meat and onions in skillet; cook until lightly brown. Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in ketchup and tomato sauce. Heat thoroughly.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cut cheese into thin strips and sprinkle over top.
Place biscuits on top and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In large Pyrex dish, put chicken on bottom or add some spaghetti, then chicken.
Mix soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese and pour over spaghetti.
Bake until bubbling.
If desired, put more cheese on top the last 5 minutes it is in oven.
If too dry, add chicken broth.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine Karo, water, salt and sugar; boil until a little tried in cold water is brittle (300°).
Beat egg whites stiff and gradually beat in the boiling syrup.
Whip until it begins to stiffen.
Add vanilla and fruit or nuts; beat more and pour into a pan slightly oiled with Mazola.
When cold, cut in squares.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger with chopped onion. Drain.
Cook noodles until tender.
Mix cottage cheese and egg. In an 8-inch square pan, alternate layers of noodles, hamburger, cottage cheese, spaghetti sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
It will make about 3 layers.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover with lid. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Will keep for several days.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Place pineapple in bowl with juice.
Add pudding.
Stir well. Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: stuffed haddock
directions: Cook rice.
Mix in Cheddar cheese and broccoli (optional) while rice is still hot.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add other ingredients until mixed.
Add 1/2 of sauce to rice and cheese mixture.
Place 1/3 cup rice mixture on the fillets; roll up.
Put remaining rice and cheese mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place stuffed haddock on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve with remaining lemon and butter sauce on the side.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: In large saucepan combine sugar and milk.
Heat to rolling boil and boil 6 minutes; stirring constantly.

title: grape delight
directions: Combine jello and water; add the pineapple with juice and the blueberry pie mix. Mix well. Pour into a 9 x 12 dish and let it set up for at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Roll ball of dough about size of a quarter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Mash down with finger tips.
Then press down with glass bottom which has been dipped in cold water (for first cookie only), then dip in white sugar for each cookie.
Bake at 375° or until light brown around edge.
Do not overbake. Baking time:
6 to 10 minutes.

title: miracle meal
directions: Brown hamburger with green pepper, onion and seasonings.
Add drained mushrooms.
Mix tomato paste and water.
Add to meat mixture with tomatoes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until cooked down.

title: easy tortilla dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and melt in microwave. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beef roast in gravy
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Place roast in a baking dish in a 350° oven with 1/2 stick of margarine; cook for 2 hours.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes with skins, then peel and mash. Mix well with remaining ingredients. Pour into a 13 x 9 dish. Add topping.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, evaporated milk and marshmallows together. Blend well and boil 8 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts. Mix well. Pour into a greased pan and cool. Cut into squares.

title: harvard beets
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add vinegar and reserved beet juice; simmer, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add beets and butter.
Serve hot.

title: quick salmon casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given; place in greased 8-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with thin white sauce.
Serves 6.

title: beef-spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Add cup of water.
Mix grated cheese, cottage cheese and eggs.
Pour 1 cup spaghetti sauce on bottom of a long cake pan.
Layer lasagne cheese mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Cut shrimp into bite-sized pieces.
Heat butter in a large Dutch oven.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Saute lightly.
Dredge okra with flour (if okra is frozen, thaw first).
Add okra to Dutch oven.
Continue to saute for a few minutes.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Lower heat, cover Dutch oven and simmer 1 hour.
Add shrimp and cook about 15 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Mix 4 to 5 tablespoons of the soup with the file, then add to soup. Stir until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Do not cook after file has been added.
Serve over a spoonful of rice in bowls.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend all ingredients, except Cool Whip, together.
Add Cool Whip and blend again.
Pour into container and freeze until time for serving.

title: corn bean salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar.
Cool.
Add oil and lemon juice if too sweet.
Toss and chill several hours or overnight.

title: rhonda's egg bake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 glass pan with Pam spray, then put the hash browns in the pan.
Cut butter or margarine and put on top of the hash browns.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When the hash browns are done, add eggs, bacon or sausage and Cheddar cheese.
Put the bacon or sausage on top of the hash browns.
Pour the beaten eggs over the meat and hash browns.
Then sprinkle the cheese over the mixture.
Bake at 350° until cheese is done, brown and bubbly.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut up vegetables and place in large bowl with lid.
Mix all other ingredients well and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, stirring now and then.
Serve as appetizer or salad.

title: oriental dinner
directions: Cut 1 pound steak (1/2-inch thick) into 2 x 1/2-inch strips. Brown in skillet in hot shortening.
Add onion, green pepper strips and mushroom stems and pieces (drain, but save liquid). Cook until tender.
Take off heat.
Move meat mixture to one side. Stir flour into drippings.
Stir in gradually 1/3 cup liquid drained from mushrooms and Pet milk.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Stir in 8 ounce can tomato sauce, brown sugar, 1 tablespoon vinegar, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Serve over 3 cups cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 5 bean casserole
directions: Add last 4 ingredients to bacon grease.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add to bean mixture.
Pour into 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lawry's dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve with veggies such as carrots, celery, broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: enchiladas(yields 12)
directions: For the sauce, brown flour in a large skillet.
Add shortening and seasonings, making a paste.
Add water gradually, then add tomato sauce and crumble in bouillon cubes.
Place in heat and cook until thick, stirring constantly.

title: savannah chicken(low in fat)
directions: Coat skinless chicken in yogurt and roll in mixture of corn flakes and sesame seed.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with Pam spray.
Line dish with chicken and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple pecan pie
directions: Let pie shell thaw 5 minutes at room temperature.
Remove shell from metal pie tin and transfer to 9-inch microwave-safe glass or ceramic pie plate, pressing dough firmly against side and bottom of pan.
Brush with egg yolk.
Prick in several places with fork.
Cook in microwave on High until shell is crisp, about 6 to 7 minutes (a few brown spots may appear).

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine the orange jello, tapioca pudding and water. Cook to a boil and then cool.
Blend together the oranges and pineapple. Add the Cool Whip. Blend with the jello mixture and refrigerate.

title: hamburg gravy
directions: Brown hamburg in skillet and drain.
Add beef gravy and 1/2 can of water. Stir and simmer on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Mash cooked carrots and add to gravy.
Serve over potatoes or noodles.

title: million dollar pickles
directions: Make brine (water and salt) to float an egg.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 2 weeks.
Take out of brine, rinse off and cut crosswise into 1-inch chunks.
Add alum, cover with cold water and let stand 24 hours.
Drain, wipe dry with cloth and put back in jar.
Make syrup and pour over cucumbers.

title: gina's german knoepfla soup
directions: In 4-quart kettle, boil chicken broth, potatoes, celery, onions and garlic.
Add cooked knoepfla.
When vegetables are almost done, add half and half, cream of celery or chicken soup, salt, pepper, celery salt and more water (if needed).
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add melted margarine, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix well and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; beat yolks slightly.
Add 1/3 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Slowly add to milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
To 1 cup of custard, add chocolate chips; stir until melted and stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.
Beat whites; add sugar and pour over chocolate mixture.
Chill until firm.
Decorate with chocolate chips to make polka dots.

title: fruit coffee cake with streusel topping
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Evenly distribute pie filling or apple slices over the batter and top with Streusel Topping.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until cake is set and topping is golden brown.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain with cold water as usual.
In large skillet melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Add 1 small onion and brown. Add hamburger, stir until brown.
Add salt.
Add tomatoes and puree.
Add spaghetti to mixture and mix well.
Cook on top of stove until it thickens.
Put into large Pyrex bowl and top it with cracker crumbs with a dash of margarine over it.
Bake in oven at 350° until crackers brown.

title: jello mold
directions: Combine jello and boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.
Chill well.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples and place in buttered baking pan.
Combine raisins and almonds.
Fill apple cavities with mixture.
Top each with 1 tablespoon brown sugar and sprinkle of cinnamon.
Combine orange juice with remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Pour into baking pan to fill halfway.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Hollow out 4 tomatoes and fill with:
1 cup Cheddar cheese, 1 cup bread crumbs, minced onion, minced parsley, nutmeg and melted butter to moisten.
Sprinkle salt on top and put tops of tomatoes back on and bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil
chicken
breasts	and remove from bone.
Cut into pieces.
Line a 7 x 11-inch buttered dish with chicken pieces. Mix soup
and
sour
cream
and pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers;
combine	with
poppy
seed
and	sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt
margarine; pour over top and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: ham salad
directions: Run ham, eggs and pickles through food chopper.
Add salad dressing and mix well.
Spread on bread or buns.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in microwave for 1 minute. Add peanut butter with chocolate. Microwave for 1 minute. Pour in buttered plate to cool.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Make cornbread ahead of time.
Saute bell pepper, celery and onions with the sausage.
Combine bouillon, chicken broth and butter.
Pour all ingredients into a large Dutch oven with crumbled cornbread.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until crust is brown on top.
Makes 12 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix together Ranch dressing mix with cream cheese and mayo. Lay out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Press ends together. Bake in oven for 10 to 13 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely. Spread mixture on top.
Add assorted vegetables and cover with shredded cheese.
Serve cold.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and onion in desired thickness.
Add milk to mushroom soup. Pour layer of potatoes and onion in buttered casserole alternately with soup.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Add paprika or cheese, if desired.

title: fig preserves with jello
directions: Break eggs into bowl; stir with fork to mix.
Do not beat; strain through a sieve.
To one cup of eggs add 1/2 tablespoon sugar.
Will keep in freezer 9 to 12 months.

title: pecan bars
directions: Cream butter.
Blend in brown sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift together dry ingredients and fold in gently. Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in slightly greased 8-inch square pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: roman holiday
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add salt, tomato soup and cooked macaroni to ground beef.
Mix well.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Heat celery and onion in skillet.
Mix all well; mold and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: to bake bread
directions: Put water in pan and sugar and yeast.
Let the yeast dissolve when it comes to top of water.
Sift flour in a baking pan and put salt, then your yeast mixture and shortening that is soft enough to mix and mix with your hands until it is stiff.
Let rise, then punch down and let rise again and put in pan.
Let rise to double and bake in 350° oven about 55 minutes.

title: chalupas
directions: Cook chicken. Cool and chop. Mix sour cream, soup, black olives, chilies, onion and half of both of the cheeses. Add chicken. Wrap mixture in each tortilla, saving some mixture to cover tortillas once arranged in casserole dish. Arrange in dish and cover with remaining mixture. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 of the cheeses. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Freezes well. Makes 10 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar, coffee and water until all sugar dissolves.
Add brandy.
Pour into 2-quart bottle.
Add vanilla bean.
Soak for 2 weeks.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, with spray cooking oil.
Heat margarine and 1 cup chocolate chips in 3-quart saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Stir in sugar, flour, vanilla, baking powder, salt and eggs until smooth.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Bake until center is set, about 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1 1/2-inch.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 36 brownies.

title: goulash casserole
directions: Layer pan with ground chuck, then layer Tater Tots.
Mix onion, salt, pepper and soup together. Pour over ground chuck and taters.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut Crisco into flour mixture to form coarse crumbs. Stir in buttermilk.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: overnight salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick, stirring constantly. Whip 1 pint of cream stiff.
Stir in the mixture with cream until smooth, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix and let stand overnight before serving.

title: farm cupcakes
directions: Mix
first
ingredients together in small bowl until smooth.
In
separate
bowl
mix remaining ingredients, except chocolate
chips.
Fill
paper-lined
muffin
tins 1/2 full of chocolate mixture.	Drop
1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture in center of
tins.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.	Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar. Add alternately the flour mixture and milk. Add extract.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in blender. Add 1/2 of the cheese to mixture and blend well. Remove from blender. Crumble remaining cheese and add to the dressing. Do not use until it has been stored 3 days in the refrigerator. It will be good as long as it lasts. Add additional milk to make it thinner.

title: no cook candy balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, Eagle Brand milk, coconut and butter well. Roll into balls.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips in pan.
Dip balls into chocolate, then drop on wax paper.
Put back in refrigerator until hard.

title: slow ball dip
directions: Hollow bread.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in clams, clam liquid, onion, Worcestershire, lemon juice, salt and pepper sauce.
Pour into bread.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours. Toast cubes in oven 5 minutes.
